title: dirt dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk together and set in fridge.
Mix all ingredients together, except cookies.
In a flowerpot, ground Oreo cookies, layer cookies and pudding mixture until all used.

title: baked sea bass steaks
directions: Mix together soy sauce, sherry, liquid smoke, chopped green onions and lemon with salt and pepper.
Marinate sea bass steaks for approximately 1 to 2 hours.

title: granny oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add sugar, cocoa, vanilla, salt, milk and peanut butter.
Bring these ingredients to a boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in 3 cups of oatmeal.
Spoon onto waxed paper.
They should become very hard.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows with butter and oil in saucepan.
Mix all other ingredients and pack in greased tube pan.
Turn out on cake plate.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie(no crust)
directions: Mix cream cheese, eggs and sugar until well blended.
Pour into 9-inch deep dish (Pyrex dish) and bake in a preheated 350° oven or slightly less for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool slightly. Once it settles down a little, spread pineapple over it.
Mix sour cream, 3 tablespoons sugar and vanilla; spread carefully over the pineapple.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes more.
Excellent!

title: granola
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes for even browning.

title: lean pie crust
directions: Stir flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add margarine. Cut with fork or pastry blender. Continue mixing until nothing sticks to side of the bowl. Shape into a ball. Wrap and refrigerate for 1 hour or more.
If prebaking, heat oven to 425°. Bake 12 minutes until golden.
This is for 8-inch pan. For a good size 9-inch pan with high fluted edge, double recipe.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Saute the diced onion in butter.
Mix the other ingredients together with the onion and butter.
Refrigerate 1 hour or for best results, refrigerate overnight.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Use an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: dill shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.
Serve with veggies or chips.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Chop dates.
Add soda and boiling water; cool.
Beat egg; add sugar, salt and vanilla and combine with date mixture.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Stir into first mixture with nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: city folks cracklin bread
directions: Mix well.
Add buttermilk to make a thin batter.
Pour into an oiled iron skillet.
Bake at 425° to 450° until browned.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix together the sugar and butter until well combined.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Beat in the eggs one at a time.
Beat in the flour mixture alternately with the sour cream.
Add the vanilla and lemon extracts and beat until combined.
Pour the batter into a greased and lightly floured tube pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for one and one half hours or until cake tests done.
Cool, then remove from pan.
Ice with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Recipe follows.

title: coconut cream dessert
directions: Mix with fork and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake for approximately 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 325° until real done.

title: hamburger patty stew
directions: Peel vegetables and slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Form beef into 24 small flat patties.
In 3-quart casserole, make layers of beef with vegetables, sprinkling layers with salt and pepper, ending with vegetables.
Add water.
Press down into casserole. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
Microwave at Medium-high 45 to 50 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 20 minutes.

title: country macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Add tomatoes, cheese and seasonings.
Heat through.

title: tasty oven stew
directions: Cook stew meat until tender.
Drain off 1 1/2 cups of the beef broth and add the Worcestershire sauce, onion, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Add the meat and rice and turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: perfect pot roast
directions: Shake flour in large size (14 x 20-inch) oven cooking bag. Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Roll down top of bag.
Add tomato sauce, water, instant bouillon, salt, pepper and mushroom soup.
Unroll and squeeze bag gently to blend.
Trim fat from roast.
Place roast in bag.
Peel and quarter potatoes, carrots and onions and add to bag.
Turn bag gently to coat ingredients with sauce.
Close bag with nylon tie.
Make 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top of bag.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/4 to 2 3/4 hours or until done.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix and pour into greased oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender. Drain and mash squash.
Mix all other ingredients well.
Put in a large buttered casserole dish.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: icebox white sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add egg and mix.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Mix in cream and vanilla.
Shape dough into roll and refrigerate overnight.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt 1 stick margarine in saucepan.
Stir in sugar, salt and milk until sugar dissolves. Stir in yeast mixture.
Beat in flour, all at once until batter is smooth, shiny and elastic.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Melt other stick of margarine in saucepan.
Punch down dough and roll out to about 18 x 12-inches.
Cut in round or diamond shapes.
Dip each piece in margarine.
Overlap each piece in ungreased tube pan.
Let rise.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until loaf gives a hollow sound.
Turn upside down on plate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: put-back potatoes
directions: Bake your potato.
Take the potato out of the oven when it's all done, wait a little bit for it to cool, then cut it in half and scoop the potato out into a bowl.
Keep one of the skins. Save 1/3 of the cheese to sprinkle on the top of the potato before it goes in the oven.
Mix the rest of the cheese, milk, salt and pepper with potato.
If you like butter, add a pat per potato now. Use the masher when potato is still a little warm.
Put mixture into potato skin.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: laura's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in water until just tender; drain.
Mix all other ingredients, except margarine and put in a large baking dish.
Stir in macaroni and chop margarine into small pieces; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in water until thick.
While hot, add other ingredients, saving 1/2 cheese to sprinkle on top of casserole before removing from oven.
Cook in buttered casserole at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon custard cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and flour.
Beat egg yolks and milk together and add to the creamed mixture.
Add lemon juice, rind and salt.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into custard cups (large ones), set in a pan of hot water and bake about 45 minutes at 325°.
Custard will settle to the bottom and cake will rise to the top.

title: how to can green beans
directions: Add salt to taste as in cooking beans.
Cover with water. After they begin to boil, let them boil for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Can and seal.
Be sure to have jars hot.

title: good for me apples
directions: Core and slice apples.
Sprinkle with brown sugar lightly over slices.
Serve with a toothpick and a glass of milk

title: crab spread
directions: Soften cream cheese and then spread on platter.
Mix seafood sauce and crabmeat and spread on top.
Serve with chips, nachos or crackers.
Can use real or imitation crabmeat.

title: marc's squash casserole!
directions: Cook squash until soft along with celery and onion.
Drain; mix bread, milk, butter, egg and cheese with squash, celery and onion. Put topping on and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop into hot oil (deep fat fryer works best).
When floats to top of oil, they are done. Serve with syrup.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in greased muffin or bread tins at 375° until done.
Make desired amount as needed.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in dish. Chill 1 hour.

title: incredible hunks
directions: Preheat oven to bake at 375°.
Combine flour, salt and soda. Stir well and set aside.
Cream butter, sugars and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Gradually add flour mixture, then add chips, nuts, raisins and oatmeal.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Mix eggs (beaten) with buttermilk, sugar and pumpkin.
Last, beat in all of the sifted dry ingredients.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Combine.
Roll into balls (about 1-inch).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool completely.

title: simple country fried chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in water, let soak for 10 minutes. Heat grease in large frying pan until hot and turn heat down to medium. Dip 1/2 of chicken pieces in flour, coating them well; place in hot grease (without pieces touching), sprinkle salt and pepper on top. Cover and let cook for 10 minutes or until golden brown, turn over and salt and pepper other side, cover for 10 more minutes. Place on paper towels to drain excess oil. Repeat process with remaining chicken.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Cream together butter, Crisco and peanut butter.
Add gradually, white and brown sugars, creaming well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls, using a rounded teaspoonful of dough for each.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten crisscrossing with fork.
Dip fork in flour to keep from sticking.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; shape into balls.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the meatballs.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all vegetables together gently. Mix and stir celery soup, cheese and sour cream into vegetables.
Put in a 9 x 11-inch dish.

title: million dollar rice salad
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add pineapple, marshmallows, rice and cherries.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: tuna salad
directions: Dice apples.
Mix first 3 ingredients; flavor with lemon juice.
Mix with enough mayonnaise to taste.
Cover, refrigerate and let stand for a short while.

title: bishop's cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in butter.
Add egg and vanilla. Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Drop dough by 1/2 teaspoon; space far apart.
Bake at 375° for about 7 minutes. Pull foil off cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Cookies will slip off when cool.
Will keep indefinitely.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Heat 1 Coca-Cola and juice drained from pineapple and cherries.
Add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add other bottle of Coca-Cola (cold).
Then add pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Chill.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream butter, eggs, honey and sugar; add milk, sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat well; fold in raisins and figs. Spoon into large loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Serve with love.

title: jeanie's chocolate pies
directions: Mix all ingredients into skillet over medium-high heat until mixture becomes thick.
Place in baked pie shells.
Beat egg whites for topping on pies.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook meat, onion and garlic.
Add Ragu sauce and simmer 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook noodles until tender.
Drain and rinse noodles.
Beat eggs; add Ricotta, 1/2 cup of Parmesan and salt. Layer half of noodles in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with 1/2 cup of Ricotta filling.
Add 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 meat mixture. Repeat layers.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix and put in freezer.
Fill to top mark.
To add flavor, add large box of jello instant pudding (any flavor).

title: easy and tasty chicken
directions: Remove all fat and skin from chicken.
Marinate chicken in soup for 6 to 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use soup over mashed potatoes after removing chicken.

title: cobbler for a lazy day
directions: *If using regular flour, add 1 1/2 teaspoons of baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon of salt.

title: cheese muff
directions: Add about 1/2 pound grated cheese to eggs, beaten in 2-quart casserole.
Lay 4 slices buttered bread in mixture in casserole. Bake in 325° oven for 3/4 to 1 hour.
Test for doneness with silver knife.
Serve immediately.
Amount of cheese and sharpness depends on your taste for cheese.

title: fruit dip
directions: Let cheese soften.
Mix all 4 ingredients.
Wonderful with apple slices.

title: tropical delight
directions: Combine cake mix, oranges, 1 package pudding mix, 1 cup pineapple and 4 eggs in large mixer bowl.
Beat for 4 minutes. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a large casserole dish.
Cook pasta according to package directions for al dente.
Mix Ricotta cheese, 1 cup of shredded Mozzarella cheese, egg, garlic and pepper.
Add cooked ziti to Ricotta cheese mixture; pour into a casserole dish and top with remaining Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes.

title: cherry jello mix
directions: Fix jello as on package.
Let set!
When firm, put in bananas and cherries.
Fold in Cool Whip and serve.

title: mock lobster
directions: Bring water, vinegar and dry ingredients to a boil.
Add frozen fish and bring to a boil.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
To serve, dip in melted butter or oleo as real lobster.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 375° until golden brown (approximately 30 to 45 minutes).
Grease pan or cast-iron skillet well before cooking.

title: hamburger macaroni casserole
directions: Make macaroni and cheese as instructed.
Brown ground chuck; pour off grease.
Add chicken soup and milk.
Put into casserole and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: taffy
directions: Cook molasses, sugar and water in a heavy kettle slowly until the mixture reaches 260° or a little of the mixture dropped in cold water becomes brittle.
Stir a little during the latter part of the boiling to prevent burning.
Pour into a buttered pan.
When cool enough to handle, cut in pieces and pull until light and stiff.
Butter the hands before pulling.

title: scalloped tuna and chips(microwave recipe)
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together. Pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Bake on High for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer cut-up chicken on bottom of pan.
Mix broth, cream of celery soup and peas and carrots.
Pour over chicken.
Add mixture of flour, milk and margarine to top and swirl in chicken.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: *May use half whole wheat and half white flour.

title: mushroom bake
directions: Rinse and pat dry, then slice mushrooms.
In a one quart casserole, combine all ingredients.
Bake covered at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, stirring once.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, heat margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot.
Add flour and stir quickly to combine, stirring constantly, gradually add milk.
Stir in salt, pepper and nutmeg. Reduce heat to low and cook, stirring frequently, until sauce is smooth and thickened, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spicy shrimp fajitas(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Saute onion and peppers in butter until crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except tortillas, and saute 5 minutes or until shrimp is pink.
Serve with warm tortillas.
If desired, top with salsa, sour cream, shredded cheese and guacamole.

title: slaw eternal
directions: Boil vinegar, oil and 1 tablespoon sugar; let it cool.
Cut cabbage, carrots, bell pepper and onion.
Add 1 cup sugar and salt.
Add the vinegar mixture to the cabbage mixture.
This will last several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: potato salad
directions: Sprinkle hot potatoes with sugar and vinegar.
Add other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: stew beef
directions: Put the stew beef in a pot, cover it with water.
Boil until the meat is cooked.
Add salt and pepper.
Add onion and tomato sauce.
Cook for 1 hour.
Add potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Serve over rice.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Arrange shrimp in a single layer in a large Corning Ware dish or sheet cake pan.
Drizzle olive oil over shrimp.
Slice margarine into pats and spread over shrimp.
Mix barbecue sauce, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, mustard, and Tabasco together and pour over shrimp.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place pan on top rack of oven.
Set oven to broil on high heat and cook for 8 to 10 minutes.
Spread newspaper on the table, supply plenty of napkins, and serve with thick slices of French bread.
Peel um and eat um.
Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add rest of ingredients. May pour seafood sauce over salad if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: super beef spaghetti squares
directions: Fry meat and drain, but reserve 2 tablespoons of grease. Sprinkle on salt and pepper.
Add chopped onions, bread crumbs and canned milk. Mix and put into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, Crisco and salt.
When lukewarm, pour over yeast.
When yeast dissolves, add eggs.
Mix well with flour.
Let rise before mashing down and rolling out. Roll on floured surface about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut.
Dip in butter and put in greased round cake pan.
Place one roll on top of another to make two layers.
Let rise about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: angel hair pasta with garlic and lemon
directions: Have large pot of water boiling for pasta while you prepare sauce.
Saute garlic in olive oil in saute pan over medium heat just until garlic begins to brown.
Remove pan from heat.
Return pan after adding wine.
Cook (simmer) for 1 to 2 minutes, until wine is reduced to half.
Stir in the lemon juice and tomato. Remove from heat.
Cook pasta in boiling water for 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Drain.
Toss pasta with basil, Parmesan cheese, pepper and tomato mixture.
Serve immediately.

title: feud cake
directions: Note:
Use self-rising flour and omit baking powder.
Will work in place of cake flour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: I usually double this and add red grapes (do not add 2 oranges).

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form small balls.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender, drain.
Mix squash, sour cream, water chestnuts, mushroom soup, pepper and salt; set aside.
Melt butter, add the Stove Top and mix well.
In a baking dish smear butter on both sides and bottom.
Put a layer of stuffing mixture then a layer of the squash mixture.
Repeat until all of squash mixture is used.
Then sprinkle the remaining stuffing mixture on top, then sprinkle almonds on.
Cook for 25 to 30 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.

title: granola bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Melt peanut butter, honey, butter and marshmallows together until marshmallows are melted.
Can add chocolate chips or M&M's (optional).

title: meatball nibblers
directions: Mix together the beef, soup mix, crumbs and egg; form balls. Bake on cookie sheet until nearly done.
Turn if needed.
Melt catsup and jelly together in a saucepan.
Add wine and meatballs; simmer for about 5 minutes.
Serve in chafing or fondue dish.

title: 1-2-3 rolls
directions: Stir together and spoon in greased muffin pan.
Cook 10 minutes at 400°.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix first six ingredients together and cook in griddle.
Top with loganberries and syrup.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Soften yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir in flour, 2 cups warm water and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Cover and let stand at room temperature for 5 to 10 days or until bubbly.
Stir 2 or 3 times daily.
Refrigerate.
Use at room temperature.

title: london broil
directions: Sprinkle meat with dry ingredients.
Let sit 1/2 to 1 hour on each side.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes per side on grill.
Last 5 minutes, baste with sauce on each side.
Slice at angle.
Cook according to thickness and desired doneness.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: Combine chicken and water in a pot; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove chicken and let cool.
Reserve 3 1/2 cups broth.
Bone chicken; chop in small pieces.
Combine chicken, broth, carrots, celery, salt and pepper in a pot.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Combine milk and flour, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add to soup mixture, stirring well.
Simmer, uncovered, until thick.
Stir occasionally.

title: barbecued water chestnuts
directions: Drain chestnuts.
Broil bacon 3 to 4 minutes.
Wrap each chestnut with 1/2 slice of bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Place on cookie sheet and broil 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Spoon on barbecue sauce and broil 2 to 3 minutes.
Turn.
Spoon barbecue sauce on that side.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and sugar.
Put in milk.
Heat until warm, then add egg yolks.
Cook until thickens. Take off eye.
Put in vanilla and margarine.
Pour in cooked pie shell.

title: american goulash(kids love this!)
directions: Brown ground beef (with onion if desired) in 9-inch skillet. Bring 6 cups of water to a boil in large pan.
Boil macaroni until done; drain.
Add corn to ground beef and stir.
Mix butter with macaroni until melted.
Stir ground beef mixture into macaroni. Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 4 to 6.
Serve with bread or roll.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: sweet 'n sour meatballs
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients into cocktail size meatballs and brown in frying pan.
Mix the rest of ingredients (except pineapple and green peppers) and add to meatballs for 20 minutes. Add the pineapple chunks and diced green peppers and cook for 10 more minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons of cornstarch and a little water to thicken.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except cucumbers, mixing until well blended.
Stir in cucumbers.
Chill several hours.
Serve with chips or veggies.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients and bake at 350° for approximately 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: amber onions
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover with lid or aluminum foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Mix marshmallows and pineapple chunks.
Chill overnight.
Whip and fold whipping cream into everything the next day.
Top with chopped nuts and cherries.

title: pound cake - mrs. has owen
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add one egg at a time, beating well.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla, mixing well.
Bake in angel food pan.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix in mixer sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla and 1 stick melted margarine.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix with hands until crumbly the pecans, brown sugar, 1 stick of margarine and flour.
Put on top of potato mixture and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Add Cool Whip to cool pudding.

title: country style steak with gravy
directions: Salt and pepper steak; roll in flour until well coated.
In deep frying pan, fry steak on medium heat in salad oil until browned on all sides.
Remove steak to side dish.
Pour off oil, leaving crumbs in bottom of frypan.
Reduce heat; stir in onion into crumbs and cook until almost done.
Add soup and water, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Return steak to mixture.
Cover and cook slowly 20 to 25 minutes on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Use gravy over rice, noodles or creamed potatoes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Partially cook chicken breasts and drain.
Partially cook broccoli and drain.
Spray an 11 x 13-inch dish with Pam.
Layer bottom of pan with broccoli and sprinkle Parmesan cheese until covered.
Next layer chicken breasts.
Mix soup with mayo, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: tea
directions: Mix together.
Store in airtight container.
To use, put 3 teaspoons into mug filled with hot water.
Adjust for your taste.

title: butterscotch delights
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour flour in; mix and press into crust.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown; cool.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Spread over crust.
Mix pudding according to directions and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with another cup of Cool Whip. Chill.

title: chocolate pudding pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip for second layer.
Combine remaining ingredients and put this mixture on top of second layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip; sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: 20 minute tamale pie
directions: Heat butter in large pan.
Add onion and meat; cook until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, corn, sour cream, cornmeal, olives and seasonings.
Stir until thoroughly mixed and cornmeal starts to thicken.
Leave in pan; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Or, pour into baking dish, sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: doggy biscuits for your pet
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; cut in margarine until mixture looks like cornmeal.
Beat sugar with egg; stir in with dough mixture.
Add approximately 1/2 cup of water.
Mix until stiff dough forms.
Roll out to 1/2 inch thickness and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 325° for approximately 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken goo
directions: Mix mushroom soup and 1 can of broth; add the rest of ingredients.
Mix well, adding more broth if it is too thick.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 12 servings.

title: brownies that cure any illness
directions: Melt butter; add other ingredients.
Bake in greased pan in 350° oven 30 minutes.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Mix all cheeses together. Add to ground onion shape on platter. Cover with chili powder.

title: lazy layer casserole
directions: Arrange all ingredients in layers in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole in the order given.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Cream the sugar, eggs and butter. Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well. Add coconut and mix.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and cook approximately 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: microwave cheese chicken
directions: Crush crackers into bottom of pan and cover bottom.
Wrap chicken in cheese and dip in egg.
Place on top of crackers. Cover with another layer of crushed crackers.
Cover pan with plastic wrap but leave room for steam to escape.
Microwave for 8 minutes; check for doneness.

title: chocolate marble bundt cake
directions: Combine cake mix, instant pudding, sour cream, eggs, vanilla and oil.
Beat well.
Divide batter into thirds.
Put one third in greased Bundt pan.
In separate bowl, put another third and add chocolate chips and chocolate syrup; stir well.
Put this mixture on top of first mixture in pan.
Add last third on top of others. Pull knife through center of batter four or five times to marbelize it.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together in a large salad bowl.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
Beat together egg, bananas and butter.
Add flour mixture and nuts.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into well-buttered muffin pans, filling each 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen large muffins.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti and cook.
Rinse with hot water; drain. Combine soup and milk in large bowl; mix well.
Add spaghetti, 1 1/2 cups cheese and remaining ingredients, except reserved cheese. Toss gently.
Pour spaghetti mixture into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: beef provencale on rice
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In frypan, heat onion for 5 minutes in butter or oil.
Set aside; brown meat.
In large casserole, place meat and blend in flour and tomato paste.
Stir in Burgundy gradually; add seasonings and mushrooms.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Add onion; bake 1 hour longer.
Serve over hot rice.

title: key lime pie ice cream
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix pie and ice cream together. Spoon into 13 x 9 dish. Sprinkle nuts and coconut on top; freeze. Cut into squares and serve.

title: spinach salad
directions: Dry spinach well; tear into bite size pieces and put into individual salad bowls.
Top with onion rings and mushrooms.
Just before serving, pour on Eileen's Salad Dressing.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put the drained pineapple in a greased dish.
Mix together the cheese, sugar and flour and sprinkle mixture over the pineapple. Put the crumbled Ritz crackers over top.
Melt the butter and drizzle over top of cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly around edges.

title: cheese and kraut crescent pockets
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 rectangles.
Press or roll each to an 8 x 5-inch rectangle, sealing perforations. Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon caraway seed over them (reserve 1/2 teaspoon for tops).
Press or roll seeds into dough.
Place 1 slice Swiss cheese, 1/4 cup kraut and 1 slice American cheese on one end of each rectangle.
Fold dough over filling and press edges to seal. Brush tops with egg; sprinkle with seeds and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 18 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and reserve.
Refrigerate pineapple.
In a medium saucepan, cook sugar, egg yolks, flour and pineapple juice over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and coats a spoon.
Remove from heat and add butter. Stir until blended.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken over rice
directions: Put rice in a large baking pan, mix the soup and water.
Pour 1/2 over the rice and stir well.
Spread chicken evenly over the rice and pour the balance of the soup over the chicken.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
If it gets to looking dry, add some water. Pour any added water evenly over all areas.

title: squash casserole
directions: Parboil zucchini for 3 to 5 minutes (you can use a combination of several kinds if you like).
Combine chopped green pepper, tomatoes, bacon, cheese, onion and salt.
Mix well.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs and blend thoroughly.
Mix in persimmon pulp, nuts and raisins.

title: gingered carrots
directions: Heat butter in a large skillet.
Add ginger and saute, stirring 1 minute.
Add carrots and water.
Cover and cook over low heat until just tender, about 15 minutes.
Add sugar and salt.
Cook, turning carrots with a spatula until liquid has almost disappeared and carrots are glazed.
Serve sprinkled with parsley if desired.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine syrup, oleo and brown sugar in a mixing bowl.
Cook on 100% power for 3 minutes.
Add soda and stir.
Cook 1 minute on 100% power.
Stir and pour over popped popcorn.

title: sheepherder's bread
directions: Stir together 1 cup flour, sugar, salt, yeast and milk.
Pour in water to moisten dry ingredients. Add margarine and starter. Beat with electric mixer at medium speed 2 minutes.
Add 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup at a time. Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Stop the mixer.
Stir in additional flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
If still too sticky, add 1/4 cup extra flour.
Knead 8 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
If sticks, sprinkle with a little flour.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Spray baking sheet with Pam.
Mix all the ingredients; roll into small balls.
Roll balls into crushed cornflakes.
Bake on cookie sheet for 15 minutes.

title: creamy lasagna
directions: Use spices such as thyme, basil, oregano and sage to taste in the sauce.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour 2 loaf pans.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into pans and bake 1 hour.
(Or use 6 mini loaf pans and bake 35 to 40 minutes.)

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Pour coconut and pecans in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over first layer. Mix melted oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar until well blended.
Pour over top of cake mix, marbleing with a knife.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Put mustard, ketchup and ground beef in pan and cook until done.
This is enough for 5 burgers.
Serve with sliced tomatoes, onions and mayonnaise.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt butter. Add cornstarch, sugar and salt; blend. Add vinegar. Cook until thick. Add beets. Heat thoroughly. Serves 4 to 6.

title: olde english prime rib(our favorite for christmas dinner)
directions: Rub seasonings and Worcestershire sauce into meat.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix jello, water and cream cheese together.
Fold in Cool Whip; put in pie crust.
Chill.

title: non-edible bread dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl with your hands.
If it is too sticky, add a little more flour.
If it's too dry, add a little more water.
Divide the dough up into 4 parts and add food coloring to each or just use the dough as is.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until it stands in soft peaks. Gradually mix in brown sugar and vanilla. Fold in pecan halves (well coated in egg-sugar mix) on greased cookie sheet 1 inch apart. Bake in 250° oven for 30 minutes. Store in air tight container. Freezes well.

title: double chocolate drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream the Crisco, both sugars, milk and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each.
Combine dry ingredients; mix with creamed mixture.
Add in nuts and chips. Spoon 2 tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart. Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet. Remove to cooling rack.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: garden chicken and stuffing
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot margarine, cook celery, onion and carrots until tender.
Add flour.
Cook 1 minute more, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in broth and milk. Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.

title: old fashioned red devil's food cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add cream, eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Use 1/2 recipe for small layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Test for doneness until toothpick comes out clean in center of cake.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in top of a double boiler. Place over simmering water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix well.
Spread candy quickly in buttered 9 x 5-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain juice off pears and heat.
Mash pears and cream cheese with fork.
Add hot pear juice to Jell-O, cream cheese and mashed pears.
Set aside and prepare Dream Whip as directed.
Add this to mixture, then nuts.
Chill.

title: dieter's delight
directions: Mix together the yogurt, pistachio pudding mix and crushed pineapple.
Pour into prepared crust and chill until firm.
May be garnished with maraschino cherries.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shrimp thoroughly.
Set aside 20 to 30 shrimp for garnish.
Coarsely chop rest and stir into mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Stir and set aside first 3 ingredients.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add flour until soft and can be kneaded.
Knead and let rise for 1 hour.
Knead and let rise again for 1 hour.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out dough to rectangle shape and spread with margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, then brown sugar and cinnamon again.
Add nuts and raisins if you wish.
Roll in jelly roll fashion and cut into 1-inch wide pieces.
Place in greased pans.
Will fit in 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan and 1 (9 x 9-inch) pan.
Let rise 30 minutes, then bake at 350° for 35 minutes until golden.

title: ham loaf
directions: Bake for
1 1/2 to 2 hours in a 300° oven.

title: quick chick trick
directions: Boil and debone chicken; tear into small pieces and line bottom of 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Combine soup and sour cream in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle crackers over top.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits in water until done.
Add garlic cheese, milk and egg.
Place in casserole dish sprayed lightly with Pam.
Bake at 300° until browned on top.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Grease wax paper with margarine and set aside.
Combine sugar and next 5 ingredients in a large heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring gently, until margarine melts.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture reaches soft ball stage or candy thermometer reads 238° (about 15 minutes).
Remove from heat, stir in pecans and flavorings.
Beat with a wooden spoon just until mixture begins to thicken.
Working rapidly, drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto prepared wax paper.
Let stand until firm.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: seashell casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: molasses crunch cookies
directions: Mix well and chill thoroughly.
Roll in small balls.
Dip in sugar.
Press flat with bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and margarine together and let boil hard for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal and peanut butter. Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and allow to set until cold.

title: sweet and spicy chicken wings
directions: Mix dressing, honey and juice together.
Set aside 1/4 cup for dipping.
Marinate chicken wings for at least 1 hour in remaining mixture.
Broil for 5 minutes.
Turn and broil for another 5 minutes.
Serve with dipping sauce.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and place in a mixing bowl. Mash thoroughly with a fork. Add cheese and mayonnaise, mixing well. Season to taste with salt, pepper, lemon juice and grated onion. Bake in a medium 350° oven until heated through. Serve with crackers.

title: lemon cloud pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, water, egg yolks, cornstarch and lemon rind in saucepan and cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
This will be rather thick. Remove from heat and add cheese.
Blend well.
Cool while preparing meringue from egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold stiff meringue into the cooled lemon mixture.
Spoon into baked shell. Sprinkle with baked pastry bits if you have any left from making your dough.
Chill 2 hours.

title: cool whip delight
directions: Combine walnuts, butter and flour and press into bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool well.

title: strawberry ambrosia salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry and raspberry gelatins in boiling water in medium bowl.
Place frozen strawberries in dissolved gelatin. Break up strawberries with fork; stir until thawed.
Stir in cold water and pineapple.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Add coconut and evaporated milk; mix well.
Pour into 5-cup mold.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Unmold.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Put cream cheese in center of tray.
Pour crab meat on top of cheese and pour cocktail sauce over that.
Serve with crackers.

title: crusty top cauliflower
directions: Place clean cauliflower in salted water to cover.
Bring to boil and cook 15 to 20 minutes (until tender).
Drain.
Place the whole cauliflower in a shallow baking dish.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard and spread it over the cauliflower.
Sprinkle until covered with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until melted and slightly brown and bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: something different salad
directions: Layer in salad bowl the first 8 ingredients.
Sprinkle with Italian Good Seasons dressing.
Put layer of mayonnaise (spread gently on top).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Toss just before serving.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Cut meat into serving slices and brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Layer thinly sliced onions over top.
Add soup (undiluted), 2 cans if you want more gravy.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covering first half of baking time.

title: super easy cheese ball
directions: Mix together; form into ball. Wrap in strips of dried beef. Refrigerate.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix flour, melted margarine, and nuts until blended. Spread and press mixture in a 9 1/2 x 13 inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool completely.

title: apple impromptu
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place apples in a well-greased 8 x 9-inch pie pan.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar with cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, cream butter and gradually add 1/2 cup sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Blend into the creamed mixture.
Spread over apples in pan.
Bake uncovered 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Great with ice cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: angel crisp cookies
directions: Combine both sugars and shortening.
Add egg and vanilla and mix well.
Combine salt, baking soda, cream of tartar and flour. Add to sugar mixture and mix well.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip top half in a dish of water then into a dish of sugar.
Place on a greased baking sheet and press down the center with finger.
Bake at 400° for 7-10 minutes.
Use colored sugar at holidays.

title: martha patch's potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, margarine and sugar; beat until fluffy. Then add vanilla, sifted flour and potato chips.
Mix lightly and drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Watch; don't get too brown around edges. Fragile.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over cookies when cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half of mixture into a greased casserole dish (deep).
Add half of the chilies and grated cheese.
Layer with rest of corn mixture; top with chilies and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until top is golden and center is set.

title: organic black bean soup
directions: Clean and rinse beans.
Place beans, water, and epazote in a 3 1/2 to 5 quart pot, and cook on medium-high for 1 to 2 hours, or until beans begin to soften.
Partially cover with lid and stir occasionally.
(Beans that are not fresh will take longer to cook.)

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain fruit; put in bowl and add the sour cream and whipped topping.
Add rest of ingredients.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti in large pot of boiling water with olive oil until al dente (almost done-soft outside, firm inside).
Drain well.
Return to pot, add Mozzarella and toss until cheese melts (cheese will be gummy and seemingly inseparable but will break up as other ingredients are added).

title: fantasy peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir together
margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 or 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to avoid sticking. Remove
from
heat;
stir
in
peanut
butter.
Add marshmallow cream
and	vanilla.
Pour	in 9 x 13-inch pan and cool at room temperature.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Mix together in a large bowl.

title: whipped rhubarb cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle on sugar and rhubarb.
Carefully pour cream on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brown derby grapefruit cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Make a well in center and add water, oil, egg yolks, grapefruit juice and lemon peel.
Beat until very smooth.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff but not dry. Gradually pour egg yolk mixture over egg whites.
Fold in gently until just blended.
Do not stir.
Turn batter into an ungreased 9-inch springform pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly with finger.
Invert onto rack and cool thoroughly.
Loosen edges of cake carefully and remove cake from pan.
With a serrated knife, cut cake crosswise to make two layers.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Pour the dry cake mix into a bowl and cut in the margarine. Add the eggs and mix well with your hands.
Roll into balls and put on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 7-10 minutes; cool.
Frost with lemon frosting.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar and add eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: baked picnic ham
directions: Wash ham; place in roaster, skin side down.
Pour remaining ingredients over ham.
Cover and bake at 400° for 2 hours and 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove skin and top fat from ham. Sprinkle with additional brown sugar.
Brown top slightly.
Cool; slice.

title: italian vegies
directions: One cup size each for large family.
Cut down for small. Place in 1-inch water over low heat.
When done, add small amount of dressing.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together peanut butter, sugar and eggs. Add margarine and mix well. Mix baking powder with flour. Add slowly to cream mixture. Bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes or until light to golden brown.

title: fresh apple pecan pound cake
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg and set aside.
In a large bowl, beat sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla at medium speed until thoroughly combined.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Pour in greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in covered bowl in the refrigerator.
Will stay good for up to 2 weeks.
When ready to use, roll out and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Bake in a 425° oven for about 10 minutes or until done.
Makes 20 to 24 biscuits. Really good!

title: pecan crunch cookies
directions: Blend well sugar, oleo and vanilla.
Add crushed chips, nutmeats and flour.
Cover and chill in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours.
Form a ball of dough and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes or until edges of cookie are light brown.
Great flavor.
(Can use stale potato chips.)

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Put corn in medium bowl. Blend flour, sugar, oleo, salt and pepper. Add to corn. Stir in green chili and cheese. Pour into an 8 x 8 greased casserole dish and bake at least 1 hour. Corn pudding is done when a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cinnamon cucumber rings
directions: Peel,
slice
and
remove
seeds
from	cucumbers.
Mix canning
lime thoroughly with enough water to cover cucumbers; let stand 24 hours.
Drain and wash well.
Soak in cold water for 3 hours; drain well.

title: sophisticated squash
directions: In casserole dish, layer as follows:
squash, tomatoes, onion, sausage and cheese.
Season with salt, pepper and desired amount of Italian seasoning.
Repeat layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(Is even better the second day!)

title: walnut cherry squares
directions: Mix first three ingredients and press into baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients. Pour into shell and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: *stuffed peppers
directions: Brown meat lightly in butter.
Add onion to meat and saute until onion is soft.
Stir in seasonings and rice.
Add 1/2 can of tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Cut tops off peppers.
Clean and remove seeds and membranes.
Stuff peppers with meat and rice mixture and place in a baking dish.
Combine remaining tomato sauce, tomato paste and remaining water.
Cover tops of peppers with some sauce and pour remainder into the baking dish.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for an additional 30 minutes.
Add additional water, if necessary.

title: date squares
directions: Cook dates, 1/2 cup sugar and water over medium heat. Stir now and then until thick. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and butter. Mix flour, oats, soda, salt, 1 cup sugar and shortening.
Mix like pie dough.
Press half (solid) dough into well-greased 8 x 10-inch or larger pan.
No flour in pan. Spread date mixture on top. Cover with rest of the dough; press firmly. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cool well.
Sprinkle generously with confectioners sugar. Cut into squares.

title: dump cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan in the listed order.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix well and marinate overnight.

title: christmas pie or cranberry goodin' puddin'
directions: Spoon cranberries into bottom of a greased 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and pecans. Set aside.
Beat eggs at high speed of an electric mixer. Add remaining 1 cup sugar and vanilla, beating well.
Add flour, butter and shortening.
Beat well.
Pour batter over cranberry mixture; bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
Yields one 10-inch pie.

title: mom's punch
directions: Mix all above except Hawaiian Punch in punch bowl.
Fill the rest of the bowl with Hawaiian Punch.
Makes approximately 2 gallons.

title: black bottom banana bars
directions: In a mixing bowl cream butter and sugar. Add egg and vanilla, beat until thoroughly combined. Blend in the bananas. Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture. Divide batter in half. Add cocoa to half. Spread into a greased 9 x 13 in. pan. Spoon remaining batter on top and swirl with a knife. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool. Cut into bars.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, butter, cinnamon, nutmeg and 1/4 cup of sugar in bowl; mix well.
Pat mixture in a 9-inch spring-form pan and chill.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In heavy skillet, cook beef with salt until browned, stirring to break into small pieces.
With slotted spoon, transfer beef to large bowl.
Add potatoes, soup, sour cream, cheese and chopped onion; mix well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown the oleo and onion.
Cook broccoli according to directions on bag.
Combine all other ingredients; stir well.
Put into casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over high heat.
Add sausage. Brown 4 or 5 minutes, stirring frequently and scraping bottom of pan.
Add chicken.
Cook for 4 or 5 minutes or until brown.
Add blackened seasoning, garlic, plus 1/2 cup each of onion and bell pepper.
Cook until vegetables start to soften, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir in rice and stock and add remainder of vegetables. Bring all to a boil and turn heat down to a slow simmer.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Pour in baking pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Have pork and ground beef ground together.
Mix all the ingredients; make into small balls.
Have water boiling with a pinch of salt.
Drop balls into water for a few minutes; fry slowly in butter until brown.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together, except 7-Up.
Add it last, then beat well.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in a 350° oven for approximately 40 minutes.
Preheat oven.

title: impossible chicken-broccoli pie(55 minutes)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Layer chicken, broccoli and cheese in greased 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients, except topping, for 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. Enjoy!

title: stir-fry carrots, cabbage and onion
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add carrots, cabbage, onion, salt, sugar and ginger.
Stir quickly until ingredients are combined.
Add water; cover and simmer 6 minutes.
Contains 57 calories per 1/2-cup serving.

title: boo bites
directions: Line cookie sheet with waxed paper.
In a large saucepan, over low heat, melt margarine.
Add marshmallows.
Cook, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted.
Remove from heat.

title: haddock and scallops casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut haddock up into smaller pieces and place into 1-quart casserole dish with scallops.

title: hot pasta cavatina
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: quiche
directions: You can use any other ingredients you want.

title: summer salad
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients into ice and let stand 3 hours. Drain.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil. Heat jars.
Can while hot.

title: macaroni saute
directions: Saute macaroni, green pepper and onion in cooking oil over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: green pea salad
directions: Toss all together and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until done (50 minutes), reserving broth.
Line bottom of casserole dish with cut up chicken.
Drain Veg-All and spread over chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix broth with cream of celery soup and pour over chicken and Veg-All.
Spoon crust mixture over pie.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.

title: fat free chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheets with Mazola cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Stir in corn syrup and egg whites until blended.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.
Each cookie:
0 gram total fat, 0 mg. cholesterol, 60 calories, 1 gram protein, 13 grams carbohydrate, 65 mg. sodium.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chow mein noodles.
Chill overnight.
Right before serving, add chow mein noodles.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: cranberry chicken(finger drumsticks)
directions: Layer single on rack in pan.
In saucepan mash cranberry sauce with fork.
Add salt and orange; cook over low heat, stirring constantly	until
sauce
thickens.
Boil 1 or 2 minutes.
Sauce is ready when it's thick and smooth.
Brush sauce over
chicken. Continue
baking and turning; brushing several times until richly glazed.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: wassail
directions: Put into pot and bring to a simmer. Serve hot.

title: super duper german chocolate cake
directions: Cook cake mix according to box directions.
Let cool completely.
Poke holes in cake (try to keep away from edges). Pour Eagle Brand milk and caramel over top. Top with Cool Whip. Crumble candy bars and sprinkle over top.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1-quart glass measuring cup, put the first 5 ingredients. Cook on High for 3 minutes and 45 seconds.
Stir and cook for 3 minutes and 45 seconds again.
Add the vanilla and margarine; cook on High for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Add the baking soda; stir until frothy.
Pour onto a buttered pan.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: dorry's soup de pasta
directions: Oil a large kettle and then place the stewing beef into the kettle.
Over medium heat, brown the meat on all sides by turning the meat often for the first five minutes.
When the meat has been browned, add 1 quart of water, salt, pepper, garlic, onions and vinegar and cook until the meat is tender.
After the meat is tender, add the vegetables and tomato sauce.
The soup concentrates as it cooks, so add another pint or two or water. When the vegetables are tender, add the ravioli and cook until they are done.
Add the two cheeses, stirring them in.

title: bushnell's chili
directions: Brown beef; add pepper and onion.
Cook.
Add salt, chili powder, pepper, cumin and allspice.
Put this with remaining ingredients in large pan.
Bring to a boil, remove from heat and add meat.
Simmer for about 3 hours.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Grate cheese and drain pineapple.
Mix cheese, pineapple, sugar and salad dressing.
This is good on crackers or on lettuce leaves.

title: bacon wrapped scallops
directions: Parcook bacon halfway so it is still soft.
Cut strips either in half or in thirds, depending on length.
Take 2 scallops and wrap in bacon (like an "S").

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook sugar, flour, egg yolks and milk over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: pop's famous chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Simmer all ingredients together for 1 hour.
Add kidney beans or chili beans (optional, not drained).
Simmer 15 more minutes.

title: garnet spritzer
directions: Pour juices over ice in a large wine glass.
Add a splash of club soda and garnish with lime slice.
Serves 1.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix well and store in glass jar in refrigerator.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Work flour, vanilla and nuts into creamed mixture.
Form into small balls.
Bake on ungreased sheet in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until very lightly browned.
Roll tarts in sugar while still warm.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: boiled frosting
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add Karo syrup that has just come to a boil to egg whites, beating constantly.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Cook zucchini 6 minutes.
Add sugar.
Cook 6 minutes.
Add lemon juice and pineapple.
Cook 6 minutes.
Take off stove; slowly add jello.
Pour into small jars.
Or pour into plastic bags and freeze.

title: potato-broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 3/4 inch cubes.
Melt margarine in 3-quart kettle.
Saute onion.
Add potatoes and bouillon water or broth.
Cook about 15 minutes until the potatoes are tender.
Set aside 1 cup of potatoes.
Puree the rest in blender and return to saucepan.
Mix in reserved potatoes and drained broccoli.
Season with salt and pepper.
Over low-medium heat gradually add cheese, stirring until heated through and cheese is melted.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: beef barley stew(slow cooker)
directions: In a skillet, brown beef and onion in oil; drain. Transfer to a 5-quart slow cooker.

Add water, tomato sauce, carrots, celery, salt, oregano, paprika and pepper. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours. Add beans, corn and barley. Cover and cook on low 2 hours longer or until barley, beef and vegetables are tender.

title: pecan cheese log
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add minced dried beef and onions; mix well.
Shape into long rolls.
Cover with pecans.
Wrap with Saran Wrap.
Chill until firm.
Slice to serve.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions; let cool.

title: spaghetti
directions: Fry hamburger meat, then drain.
Turn on medium-high heat. Put in a large pot.
Add powder mix.
Then add your tomato paste, then the Ragu.
Add about 1/2 can of tomato juice.
Boil noodles on the side.
Let the spaghetti sauce cook while stirring.
Cook until boiling hot, just a low boil.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, flour and spices.
Add soda and milk alternately with orange juice.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beef oriental(for diabetics)
directions: If time allows, partially freeze meat for easier slicing. Remove visible fat around outside of meat.
Cut meat into thin strips, 3/4-inch long and 1/8-inch thick.
Heat oil in large frying pan.
Brown meat strips, stirring with wooden spoon.
Add 1 1/2 cups hot water, beef bouillon cube, soy sauce, garlic and black pepper.
Cover and simmer slowly for 40 minutes.

title: sweet pickles(makes 4 quarts)
directions: Put
dill
in jars, then cucumbers.
Put in hot peppers and pickling
spices.
Make the brine and pour in jars.
Seal and cold
bath until cucumbers turn color.
For sour pickles, cut vinegar down to 1 cup and omit sugar (makes 2 quarts).

title: tender chocolate layer cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla at high speed until fluffy, about 5 minutes. Stir in cocoa and melted butter.
At low speed mix in flour mixture alternately with water until well blended.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread
directions: Mix together and spread on bread.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Broil.
Watch; it burns easily.
Bread should be sliced in half lengthwise and buttered before you spread mixture on.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Add milk gradually to Cheddar cheese soup, stirring until smooth.
In buttered casserole, arrange layers of potatoes, onion and cheese sauce.
Dot with butter.
Bake uncovered 40 to 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake as directed; bake in two 9-inch layer pans.
When cool, put one layer in punch bowl.
Prepare pudding.
Put 1/2 over first cake layer.
Slice bananas and put 1/2 over top of pudding. Pour 1/2 can of pineapple and juice over bananas.
Put 1 cup of strawberries, 1/4-inch deep, over pineapple.
Top with 1 carton Cool Whip.
Do the same with second layer, ending with 1 carton Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Can use any large glass bowl.

title: scrumptelicious cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
After cake cooks, mix 1 cup sugar and 1 cup milk together and bring to a boil.
Pour milk and sugar mixture over cooked cake and place in refrigerator to cool for 30 minutes.
After cake has cooled, spread the fruit (pineapple or strawberries) over top of cake.
Return to refrigerator until completely cold.
Then, spread top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pineapple zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Gradually beat in the sugar and beat thoroughly.
Stir in oil and mix until blended.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Gradually blend dry ingredients into egg, sugar and oil mixture.
Fold in the drained pineapple, walnuts and zucchini.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Remove.
Cool.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: chinese lemon chicken
directions: Combine dry gelatin, garlic salt, mustard and margarine.
Mix well.
Spread mixture evenly in ovenproof baking dish.
Place chicken in single layer over gelatin mixture, turning to coat both sides.
Cover baking dish.

title: chewy pralines
directions: Over medium low heat, cook together sugar and white syrup. Cook until candy thermometer reaches 250°.
Remove from heat and add butter and whipping cream, slowly.
Return to heat and cook until it reaches 242°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and pecans.
Drop on foil.
When cool, wrap in Saran Wrap.

title: "taco pie"
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Put chips in bottom of pie shell and layer ingredients, ending with chips. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: orange and apple stuffing
directions: Melt butter; add onion and cook until done.
Stir in some of the bread cubes.
Heat, stirring to prevent excessive browning. Turn into a deep bowl; add remaining ingredients and toss lightly. Pack stuffing loosely, it swells.

title: company potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Put all ingredients in a bowl (except cheese) and mix together.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until brown and bubbly.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: clam dip
directions: Simmer clams in broth with lemon juice for 15 minutes.
When hot, mix the rest of the ingredients together until it is somewhat thick (not too thick).
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In a 4-quart pot, saute onion and garlic in olive oil until soft.
Add broth, crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, carrots, celery, zucchini, cabbage, potato, oregano, basil, pepper and bay leaves. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: hog maw
directions: Soak pig stomach in salt
water
2 hours.
Mix sausage, potatoes, onions, salt and pepper.
Stuff
in
pig stomach and sew shut the opening
with needle and thread.
Bake covered at 250° for 5 hours.
The first hour I bake at 350°, then turn to 250° the remaining 4 hours.
The
stomach must be poked with a fork every 30 minutes.

title: pistachio pineapple delight
directions: Pour pineapple and juice in bowl; add pudding mix.
With wire whisk, rotary beater or electric mixer, mix at lowest speed.
Beat until well blended.
Fold in whipped topping and nuts.
Spoon into dessert dish.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: First Layer:
Spread cooked chicken over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Place broccoli flowerets in a large bowl.
Add raisins, pecans, onion and bacon.	Stir to mix.
Add mayonnaise mixture; toss lightly to coat.
Serve immediately or cover and chill until serving time. Makes 6 side dish servings.

title: summertime rice salad
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Add celery, pickle, onion, parsley and mustard.
Mix well.
Cover and chill about 1 hour.
Add mayonnaise.
Serve on crisp lettuce.

title: lemon honey butter
directions: Mix until smooth and fluffy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put onion mix in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice over soup. Layer chicken pieces on top of rice.
Dilute soup with stock and pour over chicken.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: "souper" meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Shape into a loaf in an 8 x 11 1/2 x 2-inch or larger pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. (Cracker crumbs may be substituted for bread crumbs.)

title: lindsey's pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Cream butter, gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla, mix well. Alternate additions of dry ingredients and pumpkin, after each addition. Stir in morsels. Drop onto
greased cookie sheet. Bake for 15 minutes.

title: sweet onion casserole
directions: *These fresh, big, sweet onions can be Walla-Walla, Vidalia or Texas sweets.

title: pepperoni and chive muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except pepperoni.
Stir until just moist.
Fold in pepperoni. Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.

title: hot potato scalloped salad
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl.
Add cheese, broken in small pieces, and bread.
Mix lightly so potatoes are not mashed. Season and put into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour melted butter and milk over mixture and sprinkle with cornflakes.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tangy salad dressing
directions: Combine and shake.
Allow to stand for 1 hour before serving.

title: evie's western cake
directions: Have eggs and oleo at room temperature.
Cream oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour gradually.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Then invert pan.

title: creamy orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Gradually add to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Stir in juices and orange rind.
Pour into a 1-quart mold; chill until firm.
Unmold. Surround with lettuce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: applesauce crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Make crumbs of crackers and mix with melted margarine and brown sugar.
Finely chopped nuts may be added, also.
Set aside.
Combine the applesauce and spices.
Pour half into buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Top with half of crumbs, rest of applesauce and top with rest of the crumbs.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Serve hot or cold with ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: eggplant spaghetti
directions: In large skillet, heat oil on medium heat.
Add eggplant, onion, garlic and parsley.
Cook until transparent and tender (about 5 minutes).
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, salt and sugar.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over spaghetti and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine and boil 1 stick oleo, oil and water.
Pour over sugar, flour and cocoa; then add eggs, buttermilk, salt, soda and vanilla.
Mix well by spoon.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken dumplins
directions: Cook chicken with skin, then remove skin and bones.
Set aside.
Take biscuits and roll on floured cloth and cut in small strips.
Add to boiling broth (one at a time) and cook until tender.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Cook a few minutes more.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 40 balls.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on package.

title: smudgy squares
directions: Melt the margarine and marshmallows together; remove from heat.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan (pan should be greased).
Ice with a thin layer of chocolate icing.
Cut into squares.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to package directions.
When done, add butter
or	margarine
and garlic cheese.
In a measuring cup, beat
eggs.
Add
enough
milk to make 1 cup.
Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and grated cheese (optional).	Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Brown onions in small amount of butter or oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°, stirring once and adding water, if dry.
(Can also be made on top of the stove in a covered saucepan until rice is tender, 45 to 60 minutes.)
Serve topped with dollop of sour cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash.
Blend onion, soup, sour cream and carrots with squash.
Melt butter and pour over bread crumbs.
Put half of bread crumbs in bottom of greased baking dish.
Add squash mixture.
Top with remaining bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 or 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit pizza pie
directions: Roll out thawed pastry and place on pizza pan; dough should exceed 1-inch over edge.
Prick with fork and bake 20 minutes in 350° oven or until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix sugar and cream cheese until creamy and spread over cooled pastry.
Arrange sliced fruit over filling.

title: joan's dip(easy appetizer)
directions: Mix; melt slowly, top of stove or microwave (Low).
Refrigerate until "jelled."
Serve with crackers, chips, whatever.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook on 450° until done.

title: shirley's casserole(bread)
directions: Saute onions in one tablespoon oil for about 2 minutes.
In mixing bowl, combine biscuit mix and ham.
Mix remaining oil, eggs, milk, mustard, onion and half of cheese and sesame seed. Add this to ham mixture and mix well.
If you are baking these in mini muffin tins, add remaining cheese and butter to mixture.
If baking in a casserole dish, top with remaining cheese and butter. Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350° as a casserole; bake muffins approximately 20 minutes at 350°.

title: healthy yogurt cookies
directions: May need to add 1/2 cup low-fat milk.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss ingredients together and spread in shallow baking dish. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Top with sharp Cheddar cheese and toasted almonds.
Return to oven to melt cheese.
Serves 6.

title: linguine and clam sauce
directions: Drain clams.
In medium saucepan, cook onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in 2 (16 ounce) cans of tomato sauce with tomato bits, oregano, salt, pepper, drained clams, parsley and wine.
Heat through.
Serve over linguine.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: quick vegetable bake
directions: Drain mixed vegetables.
Put in casserole.
Add corn and liquid, onion, mayonnaise and Cheddar cheese.
Mix crushed crackers and butter; sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Place brown sugar and pecans in baking pan, arrange pineapple slices over brown sugar and nuts.
Dot with butter.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat egg yolks and white sugar until fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture, vanilla and pineapple juice alternately.
Fold in beaten egg whites, pour over mixture in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Leave in pan a few minutes; turn upside down.

title: western corn salad
directions: Mix and serve cold.

title: vicki's peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Melt margarine in 8x12 inch baking dish.
Sift together flour, 1 cup sugar, salt and baking powder.
Blend with milk.
Pour mixture over melted margarine. Spread peaches over this and sprinkle with other cup of sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Crust will magically appear and cover entire surface of cobbler.
Serves 6.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Place Fritos, then chicken, then onions in dish.
Mix and heat in saucepan the soup, cheese and the Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Sprinkle garlic salt over mixture and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: dot's pound cake
directions: Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour three 9-inch cake pans.
In large bowl, cream together the butter, shortening, and sugar.

Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, salt, and baking soda. Stir to mix. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk. Add vanilla and beat until blended. Pour into prepared pans. Bake about 25 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of cake layers.
Remove from pans and cool completely on racks.
Frost with either the cooked peanut butter icing or the quick and easy peanut butter icing.

title: chocolate-pecan pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Let cool slightly.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt, stirring well.
Stir in 1/2 cup pecans and coconut; pour filling into unbaked shell and top with remaining 1/2 cup pecans.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes. Yield:
one 9 inch pie.

title: good dessert
directions: Bake cake; cool.
Mix pudding and cream cheese.
Spread over top of cake, pineapple and Dream Whip.
Top with nuts, if desired.

title: pineapple baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix beans, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, catsup and drained juice.
Place in casserole dish and top with pineapple.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: pancit
directions: Saute onion and garlic powder in hot cooking oil.
Add chicken and season with soy sauce and pepper.
Fry for two minutes.
Add all the vegetables and keep stirring for a few minutes.
Pour broth over chicken and vegetables.
When vegetables are half cooked, add noodles and cook, stirring, until noodles are done and most of the broth is absorbed.
Serve hot.

title: barbecue steak
directions: Brown steak in large heavy frying pan about 1 minute on each side.
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour over steak pieces and simmer until steak is tender, about 2 hours.
Cook on high for a few minutes if sauce is not thick enough.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: stuffed jumbo shells
directions: Saute chopped meat in olive oil.
Mix with egg, cheese, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour half sauce in baking dish. Stuff shells with filling.
Top with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan butterscotch fudge
directions: Grease a 9-inch square pan.
In a 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar, evaporated milk, marshmallows, butter and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture starts to bubble. Reduce heat to a very low temperature and cook 5 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and quickly add the nuts, butterscotch chips and vanilla.
Stir until chips are completely melted.
Immediately pour mixture into pan and, if desired, decorate the top of fudge with large pecan pieces.
Makes 3 dozen 1 1/2-inch pieces.

title: hunter's casserole
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a skillet.
Saute the onions for 10 minutes.
Add the meat; cook over high or medium high heat, stirring frequently, until browned.
Mix in the salt, pepper, nutmeg and broth.
In a greased 2-quart casserole, arrange as many layers as possible of the potatoes, meat mixture and apples, starting and ending with the potatoes.
Sprinkle with the bread crumbs; dot with the remaining butter.
Bake at 375° oven temperature for 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tattie (potato soup)
directions: Add diced carrots, turnips, chopped leeks and seasonings to stock.
Bring to boil.
Simmer covered 1 hour.
Add diced potatoes, grated carrot and simmer another hour.
Garnish with parsley.

title: impossible broccoli pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2 inches. Rinse broccoli under cold water to thaw.
Drain thoroughly.
Then mix broccoli, 2 cups cheese and onion in the plate.
Then beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth for 15 seconds in the blender, or on High for 1 minute with hand mixer.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake just until cheese melts, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Garnish with tomato slices if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
In a skillet, put butter, marmalade, water and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add carrots and cook over moderate heat, basting frequently, until glazed.

title: turkey soup
