directions: Boil turkey carcass, onion, carrots and celery in a full pot of water.
Remove carcass.
Add corn, tomato sauce and barley. Season with salt, pepper, dill and parsley to taste.
Enjoy!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Put in bottom of pan or casserole dish.
Add ham and soup and cover with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dinner rolls
directions: *By using cottage cheese instead of shortening or cooking oil, you can cut down on the fat, yet still achieve a tender and moist bread.

title: candied dills
directions: Drain pickles and
cut
in lengthwise strips, slices or chunks.
Combine sugar
and
vinegar;
add
pickling
spices. Place pickles in bowl or
jar and cover with the syrup.
Cover and let stand for several days.
Stir every day.
Remove spice bag and pickles are ready.

title: good caramel corn
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients
to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add soda, cream of tartar and salt. Pour over the popped corn. Stir until covered.
Bake 1 hour at 200°.
Shake or stir with wooden spoon every 10 to 15 minutes while baking.

title: tropical smoothie
directions: Blend strawberries, pineapple and yogurt in blender. Gradually add ice cubes, turning blender on and off until ice is crushed.

title: mam-maw mize's chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Stir.
Add milk and butter.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Pour in pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Brown in oven.

title: buttermilk and cucumber
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on high until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 1 cup.

title: turkey goulash
directions: Brown ground turkey in good sized pan.
Break up with a fork into tiny pieces.
Drain any fat.
Add tomatoes, baked beans and kidney beans to turkey, rinsing out each can with plenty of water, dumping water into pan.
Add dried onions and bell pepper.
Stir all.
Cook about 10 minutes on low.
Stir; add barley.
Stir; cook 20 minutes more.
Lower heat as low as you can.
It can be on burner until you are ready to eat it.
It can set a long time on very low heat.
Stir occasionally.

title: 90 and 9
directions: Fry and simmer meat in butter. Boil noodles in salt water and drain. Add soup, cheese, pimentos, green pepper, mushrooms and corn to noodles. Mix together with meat and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven. This will serve 12 to 15.
For smaller dish, use half quantity, except for meat.

title: punch-strawberry delight
directions: Marinate strawberries in wine and sugar for 12 hours before serving.
Add champagne or sparkling water. Decorate with mint. Serves 30 to 35.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all in mixer.
Beat for 3 minutes. Pour into greased, floured 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: quick quiche
directions: Beat all the above ingredients (without baking soda) in the blender.
Beat well.
Add the baking soda and beat again until the dough stops rising.
In a greased and floured Pyrex, pour half of dough and then pour 1 of the last ingredients. Pour the rest of dough over the top.
Bake until light brown.
Enjoy!

title: perfect char-grilled filet mignon(serves 2)
directions: Pour the salad dressing into a shallow pan. Place the steaks in the pan and let them marinate for 3 to 4 hours.

title: baked squash
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender. Drain and mix cheese, jalapenos, salt and pepper. Pour into buttered baking dish. Bake 20 minutes. To make it spicy add more jalapenos.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Add cheese and 1/2 stick butter.
Mix broccoli, cheese and butter until cheese is melted. Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Add 1 package Town House crackers, crumbled.
Mix with 1/2 stick melted butter over top (sprinkle).
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: zucchini
directions: Wash and slice (with peel on) about 1/4 inch thickness.
Dip in beaten egg and then in flour.
Cook slowly in margarine in electric skillet (or regular skillet).
I have more even heat in my electric skillet.
Salt lightly.
Cook until not crunchy anymore and brown on both sides.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Place cream cheese in a 1-quart casserole; microwave at High for 1 minute, stirring after 30 seconds.
Stir until cream cheese is smooth and creamy.
Stir in milk, sour cream, onion, garlic powder, pepper, chopped green pepper and chopped dried beef, mixing well.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together.
Garnish with lemons, frozen strawberries, oranges or sherbet ice cream.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Put eggs in blender.
Add Pet milk, vanilla and sugar to taste. Blend well and pour into freezer.
Add enough sweet milk to fill freezer.
Freeze.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs; mix well.
Pat over bottom of pan.
Combine eggs, 2 sticks softened butter and confectioners sugar in a mixer bowl. Beat 12 minutes.
Spread in prepared pan.
Top with bananas. Spoon pineapple over bananas.
Spread whipped topping over all. Sprinkle with pecans.
Chill 8 to 10 hours.

title: chop suey cake
directions: In a large bowl (not mixer), combine flour, sugar, eggs, baking soda, pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Mix with wooden spoon until thoroughly moist and combined.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until puffed and browned on top.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together the flour, salt, soda and sugar.
Add butter, eggs, bananas and nuts.
Add to mix the 1/2 tablespoon vanilla. Mix thoroughly. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Small pans, makes 6 pans.
For 2 regular loaf pans, bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Spread pie filling in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or pie dish. Sprinkle cake mix from box over cherries.
Pour melted butter over top and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
(It will be runny and look not done.)
Serve warm with whipped cream. Delicious!
Serves 12.

title: microwave cauliflower
directions: Cut core out of bottom of cauliflower.
Rinse whole head with cold water and shake, leaving some water on head.
Do not dry. Place in microwave-safe dish and cover with Saran Wrap.
Cook on High for 12 or 15 minutes or until fork-tender.
Time depends on size of cauliflower.
Remove Saran Wrap.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard and cheese together and spread on head.
Microwave until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy. Add all other ingredients except zucchini and nuts.
Beat well. Fold in zucchini and nuts.
Put in 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Use small muffin pan.
Mix well and roll in walnut size balls; put in pan and spread up sides to make cups.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine pudding mix and gelatine.
Cook according to directions on the pudding package using 2 1/4 cups of milk.
Remove from heat and cover with waxed paper; set aside.

title: one-rise monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease (not oil) a 12-cup fluted tube pan.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, blend 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast, water, margarine and egg at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour.
Knead dough on floured surface until smooth, about 1 minute.
Press or roll dough to a 15 x 20-inch rectangle.
Using pastry wheel or sharp knife, cut dough into diamond shape pieces by cutting into 1 1/2 to 2-inch strips diagonally across dough.
In a shallow pan, melt 1/3 cup butter.
Dip each piece in melted butter and layer in prepared pan, overlapping the pieces.
Sprinkle each layer with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Do remaining pieces of dough the same way, making several layers.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until light and doubled in size, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until deep, golden brown.
Cool 2 minutes.
Invert onto serving dish.
Serve warm.
Makes a 10-inch ring pull-apart loaf.

title: never fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In medium saucepan, stir sugar, milk and salt.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Add butter.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter. Beat well and pour into pan.
Cool.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugars, corn syrup, vanilla and eggs.
Mix in oats, M&M's and chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 13 to 14 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: grandma's molasses cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Stir in molasses and milk.
Combine flour, salt, ginger, cinnamon, cloves and soda. Mix into wet ingredients.
On floured surface, roll 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter (2-inch).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: aunt mina's breakfast casserole
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13 baking pan.
Spread sausage in pan. Combine eggs, soup, mustard, milk and pepper.
Pour over sausage. Top with cheese, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove cover, sprinkle with croutons and bake uncovered at 350° for 45-60 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over 1/4 cup lukewarm water; let stand for a few minutes.
Pour the hot water over the sugar, salt and Crisco; let stand after mixing until lukewarm.
Add the beaten eggs, then the yeast.
Add the flour, a cup at a time, until you have a batter thick enough to knead.
Knead for about 5 minutes.
Put in a large bowl and let rise 1 1/2 hours or until double in size. Cover the bowl with dish towel.
Work down; shape into rolls or 3 loaves of
bread.
Cover and let rise about 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush with butter.

title: chiffon pumpkin pie
directions: Add pie filling to milk and beat slowly until well blended. Blend in pumpkin spice and 2 cups whipped topping.
Pour into pie shell and chill until set.
Garnish with whipped topping and pecans.

title: barley beef vegetable soup
directions: In 5 quart pan, cook beef, onion and garlic over medium-high heat until meat loses its pink color and onion is limp.
Drain and discard fat.
Add carrots, celery, basil, oregano, barley and broth.
Bring to boil; then reduce heat, cover and simmer gently for about 45 minutes or until barley is tender.
Add zucchini and simmer just until tender, about 5 minutes longer.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Garnish with parsley when served.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Combine first five ingredients and dredge in 3/4 cup flour, mixing well.
Set aside.
Cream butter or margarine in large bowl; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of mixer.
Add eggs and jelly, mixing well.
Dissolve soda in milk; add to creamed mixture.
Add remaining 3/4 cup flour and spices; mix well.
Fold nut and fruit mixture into batter.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes or until done.
Cool on wire racks.
Yields 12 dozen or 144 cookies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts in bowl, mixing thoroughly, then add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy corned beef bake
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients. Transfer to a greased 2-quart baking dish. Toss bread cubes with butter; sprinkle over top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole(salad)
directions: Cut up cauliflower, broccoli, onion and green pepper.
Mix together with sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Refrigerate.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: eggnog cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Dust lightly with flour. Set aside.

title: burger for a bunch
directions: Combine 1/4
cup
potato flakes with butter.
Set aside in large mixing
bowl.
Combine
1/4 cup potato flakes, flour, sugar, cream of
tartar and soda.	Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk and mayonnaise; blend until a soft dough forms.
Divide in half; roll one half to a 9-inch circle and put on	greased cookie sheet or pie plate.
Spread filling to within 1/2
inch
of edge; sprinkle with a cheese. Roll out remaining dough.
Place on top scalping edges.
Brush with milk.
Sprinkle with
buttered
potato
flakes.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a golden brown.

title: pear coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease and flour an 8-inch round pan.
Mix baking mix, sugar, butter and milk. Pour into the pan.

Arrange pear slices in circular pattern on batter; sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and toothpick inserted comes out clean. Cut into wedges and spoon yogurt on top of each serving. Serves 8.

title: cheese balls
directions: Let cheese soften; chop pepper, onions, pimentos and pecans real fine.
Mix all ingredients together (except pecans).
Form into balls and roll in pecans.
Chill and serve with favorite crackers.

title: short cut cake
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl.
Mix well.
If it needs extra liquid add 1/4 cup water.
It will depend on the size of the eggs how much liquid you need, if any.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Add nuts if you like.
Put in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until top of cake springs back as you mash the top.
Cooking time:
Approximately 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Put 1 slice cheese on each breast.
Mix soup with wine.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle 2 cups herb stuffing mix on top.
Drizzle butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: one pan salmon dinner(low-fat)
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots in broth in large skillet 3 to 4 minutes.
Add green beans, salt and pepper.
Place salmon on vegetables.
Sprinkle with dill.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes on medium-low heat until fish is opaque in center.
Serve in soup plates with broth.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix cocoa in hot water to make a smooth paste; set aside to cool.
Mix together sugar and shortening, then add eggs and beat. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk, then stir in chocolate and vanilla.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no spoil potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes (leave skins on) and cool.
Chop dill; add to potatoes.
Combine rice vinegar and oil; shake.
Toss on potatoes. Mix and eat!

title: coconut kisses
directions: Beat egg whites with dash of salt until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar, beating to stiff peaks. Add vanilla. Fold in corn flakes and coconut (and nuts, if desired).

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown beef, celery, onion and green pepper and drain.
Add tomatoes, beans and seasonings and cook until thickens a little.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and margarine together, then press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling on top.
Mix Dream Whip according to package, then beat in cream cheese and spread on top of pie filling.
Chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water; drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients, except for 1/2 of stuffing, butter and cheese.
Mix well.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased shallow baking dish. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Serve hot with chips or crackers.

title: dressing for turkey or chicken
directions: Put margarine, celery and onion in a small skillet; cook until golden.
Mix this with bread, eggs and seasonings.
Add liquid and mix until all the bread is quite moist, but not runny.
Taste and re-season, if necessary.
Use to stuff bird or bake in a dish in the oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix until fluffy the eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Mix all together. Bake in an ungreased sheet cake pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: southern tea
directions: Boil water and sugar.
After tea steeps add to other ingredients.

title: hungarian chicken
directions: Microwave onions and green pepper for 2 minutes.
Add to this mixture the tablespoon paprika, garlic powder, mushrooms and soups.
Blend into the chicken and broth and simmer until it comes to a boil and the chicken is thoroughly heated.
Thicken with cornstarch mixture and remove from heat.
Add frozen peas, if desired.
Just before serving, blend in the sour cream.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread marshmallows over bottom of pan about 1-inch apart.
(They're for the icing.)
Bake in a 350° oven until cake tests done.

title: knox blox
directions: In large saucepan, sprinkle gelatine over cold water; let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
Stir in jello, stirring frequently.
Bring to boil.
When jello is dissolved, pour into 8 x 12-inch pan.
Refrigerate to set.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix for a few minutes.
Bake in two medium size loaf pans at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: cheesy green onion muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 18 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups. Cut and separate cream cheese into 1/4 inch cubes; set aside.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Cook to soft ball stage; add sugar, cocoa, salt and sour cream.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook slowly over low heat, stirring constantly, until all the cheese has melted.
Pour mixture over drained mostaccioli and mix well.
Pour into baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onions and tops, celery, water chestnuts and peas in bowl.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and then layer in order, mayonnaise, tomatoes, eggs, bacon and Parmesan cheese.
When ready to serve, toss.

title: granny collier's chewies
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve when cool.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Make jello and combine strawberries, bananas and pineapple. Chill 1/2 of mixture.
When set, spread with sour cream.
Add remaining mixture and chill.

title: egg casserole
directions: Cover bottom of greased dish (10 x 15-inch) with bread.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over bread.
Put grated cheese on top and cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Watch carefully so bottom doesn't get too brown and eggs are set.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon crisp and crumble.
Reserve 1/4 cup drippings. Peel potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place potatoes on 24 x 18-inch rectangle of heavy-duty foil.
Combine salt, pepper, celery seed, sugar, flour and onion flakes; sprinkle over potatoes.
Combine vinegar and reserved bacon drippings; pour over potatoes.
Add radishes, if desired.
Sprinkle bacon over top. Fold foil and seal tightly.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 425° for 1 hour.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: herbal rolls
directions: Melt butter, add dill seed, parsley and cheese.
Separate biscuits and cut into quarters.
Toss biscuit pieces in butter mixture.
Flatten biscuit pieces so edges touch in pan.
Bake at 425° about 20 minutes.
Very good for appetizers.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 pan.
Dump ingredients one item at a time in order on top of each other
in the pan. DO NOT STIR.

title: winter food for the birds
directions: Put lard, peanut butter and suet in double boiler and melt. Pour over dry ingredients and mix.
While still hot, pour in containers (cottage cheese cartons or tuna cans; plastic is best). You can also pour this into pine cones to hang up.
Serves about 731 birds.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Chop the zucchini and onion; mix them with salt and let stand overnight.

title: apple blossom cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs until well mixed.
Stir in vanilla, nuts and chopped apples.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir in batter until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until brown.

title: lemon cookies or key lime cookies
directions: Add juice to egg and beat with fork, then add oil and cake mix. Use an electric mixer to cream the batter.
Scoop out batter by teaspoonful and place 2-inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Place a pecan half or slice of cherry on top.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9 or 8 x 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs into butter.
Layer coconut, butterscotch chips, chocolate chips and pecans.
Drizzle top with Eagle Brand milk. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Allow to cool completely before slicing.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly first 4 ingredients.
Then add next 5 ingredients and mix.
Form into balls and place about 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes at 375°.
Do not overbake.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: dirt cake
directions: Note:
Need 1 medium size flowerpot (8-inch, plastic), 1 bunch artificial flowers and 1 small shovel (optional).

title: catherine's slush
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Add frozen orange juice, cold water and crushed pineapple.
Mix thoroughly.
Remove from heat.
Slice bananas and chop whole jar of cherries and add to liquid mixture.
Stir mixture and pour into plastic container with a top.
Put in freezer until frozen.

title: homemade orange sherbet(4 quart recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in ice cream freezer.

title: fish fillets stuffed with shrimp
directions: In a skillet, melt butter and add chopped celery and onion; saute until tender.
Reserve 1/2 cooked shrimp and chop fine the other half.
Combine with celery and onion.
Stir in the bread crumbs, egg and 3 teaspoons of Worcestershire sauce; mix well. Place stuffing on each fillet; roll tightly and fasten with toothpicks.
Place in shallow baking dish; set aside.

title: african chow mein
directions: Sauce celery and onions in 1 tablespoon oil.
Take out and put meat in pan.
Brown well.
Combine all other ingredients and bake in a 3-quart casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: drumstick dessert
directions: Mix 2/3 cup of peanuts, wafers and melted butter together. Put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool. Mix cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar until smooth. Fold in 2 cups Cool Whip.
Layer over crust and refrigerate.
Mix pudding and milk.
Pour in pan over first mixture and refrigerate. Put rest of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with remaining peanuts and candy bar (grated).

title: amish steak
directions: Mix ingredients (except soup and 1 can water) and pat into a cookie sheet with sides.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in 3 x 3-inch squares.
(You may freeze squares at this point to be used later.)
Roll squares in flour.
Brown.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover with beefy mushroom soup and water.
Cover with foil. Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Take foil off for the last 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli from 8 to 10 minutes in salt water.
Drain water, add cheese and 1/2 stick butter.
Stir until melted.
Pour in buttered casserole dish.
Crush crackers and melt remainder of butter and add crumbs.
Pour over top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy 2
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together and shape into small balls. Put on ungreased cookie sheet and cook 10 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix and boil ingredients, then add 4 cans of medium beets and heat thoroughly.

title: pear preserves
directions: You will need jars and seals.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Oil large shallow baking dish. Cut tomatoes horizontally and place cut side up in the dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Combine parsley, basil and garlic and sprinkle over the tomatoes. Drizzle 1/4 teaspoon of oil on each tomato half. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve warm or room temperature. Makes 6 servings, 1 tomato each.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Chop corned beef in a mixing bowl.
Stir in onion or vegetable dip package.
Add in sour cream and stir.
Then add mayonnaise and stir.
Mixture should be very smooth.
Cut a round hole in the Hawaiian bread and set aside.
Pour corned beef mixture into the center of the bread.
Cut the bread that was removed from round loaf into bite-size pieces for dipping in the corned beef dip. Great appetizer for football games or small parties.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix well in bowl.
Form into balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Place in fridge until chilled.

title: daffodil dip
directions: Blend ingredients with a fork. Crumble yolk of the hard-cooked egg and crumble on top.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all together in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° until hot.

title: shish kebab
directions: Marinate steaks all day or overnight.
In bowl, prepare mix according to package directions.
Add beef; marinate in refrigerator.
Add vegetables to beef, toss to mix and marinate about 10 minutes.
Arrange meat and vegetables alternately on skewers, packing tightly.
Broil or grill to desired doneness. Good with cooked rice and hot rolls.

title: deviled dip
directions: Blend all ingredients. Serve with potato chips or crackers. Makes 2 cups dip.

title: strawberry yogurt dip
directions: Combine together and chill.
Serve as a dip for fruit.

title: banana split cake
directions: Layer first 2 ingredients for crust (13 x 9-inch dish). Mix butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Layer bananas.
Top with pineapple,	then
Cool
Whip,
pecans, cherries and chocolate. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli and bacon quiche
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in blender.
Put half of cheese in pie shell.
Add broccoli, onion and bacon on top of cheese.
Top with remaining cheese, then pour mixture from blender over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hulse's favorite stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole with a cover and bake 5 hours at 250°.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ingredients except cheese (do not drain broccoli).
Pour batter in pan; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter, oil and sugars in large bowl; mix well.
Add eggs; beat 1 minute until well blended.
Add vanilla; beat well. In separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda and cream of tartar; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, water and sugar until berries pop.
Stir in jello and let cool.
Add grapes, nuts and pineapple.
Refrigerate until firm.
Great for the holidays.
Use Cranberry Salad in place of cranberry sauce for holiday dinners.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fold all ingredients together and bake in greased casserole. Top with 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese, 1/2 stick butter and 1 cup stuffing mix.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole #2
directions: Crumble 3 slices of bread and place in bottom of casserole. Chop chicken and place over crumbs.
Combine mayonnaise, eggs, milk, chopped peppers, celery, onion and salt.
Pour over chicken. Spoon soup over all.
Crumble 3 remaining slices of bread and put on top.
Chill one hour or overnight.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: quick sour cream rolls
directions: In large mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk,
sour
cream,
cups
of flour, shortening, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping
bowl
occasionally.
Stir
in remaining flour.
Turn dough onto well floured board and knead 5 minutes or about 200 turns
(shape
immediately).
Let
rise
1 hour before baking. (Dough is ready if impression remains.) Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine; mix all other ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Cook to 250° or hard boil stage.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish that has been buttered.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl beat eggs foamy.
Add flour and sugars.
Beat.
Blend in butter.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake in 1 hour.
Serve warm.
Recipe may be doubled.
Freeze 1 pie for later.

title: five-cup salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Combine with coconut and marshmallows in serving bowl.
Stir in sour cream.
Chill for several hours.
Yields 5 servings.

title: mammy's sour milk biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in butter. Add milk to make a soft dough. Knead about 20 turns; roll to a 1/2-inch thickness and cut with a 2-inch cutter. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 12 to 14 biscuits.

title: italian dessert
directions: Beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Put half in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread filling on batter.
Top with rest of batter.
Bake 35 minutes in 375° oven.

title: spicy cereal crunch
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a heavy skillet. Stir constantly over medium heat until boiling.
Boil 3 minutes.
Can do in microwave.
In a buttered large bowl, toss the cereal, raisins and nuts.
Pour hot syrup over cereal mixture.
Stir to coat.
Spread on 2 buttered baking sheets.
When firm, break into pieces.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine.
Dip chicken in margarine.
Roll chicken in Ritz crackers.
Place chicken in casserole dish; cover with leftover Ritz crackers and margarine.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Take foil off.
Bake for 5 minutes, until golden brown on top.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Shell shrimp; cut out vein along outside curve.
Rinse, drain and refrigerate shrimp until ready to use them.
Cut green peppers into 1/2-inch pieces.
Chop onions.
Place all vegetables in automatic skillet or large, regular skillet; add oil and saute at 375° (medium heat) until tender.
To tender vegetables, add salt, pepper, paprika, Tabasco and tomatoes.
Cook at 225° (medium-low heat) 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp and cook just until shrimp get done.
Turn automatic skillet to 150°.
Mound shrimp mixture in center of skillet.
Add parsley to cooked rice; spoon ring of rice around shrimp.
(Or transfer shrimp from regular skillet to platter and surround with rice.)
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in water until firm (more water may be added). Add onion, pepper, salt, garlic and milk.
Cook until milk is hot. Add bacon and ham.
Mix flour and butter together in a bowl until mixture becomes thick and brown in color.
Stir in soup a little at a time briskly.
Make sure soup is hot when adding.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Repeat the process if soup is not thick enough.

title: fluffy waffles
directions: Mix batter and pour into waffle iron.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Let set together in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Bake white cake mix; cool.
Split cake so you have 4 layers.
Put coconut mixture between layers.
Wrap in Saran Wrap, then foil.
Let set in refrigerator for 3 days.

title: quicky stroganoff
directions: Drain steaks and cut into 1/4-inch wide strips.
Brown strips in hot oil.
Add mushrooms and onion soup mix.
Heat to boiling. Put the flour into the sour cream and blend.
Combine with first mixture.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Sauce will be thin.
Serve over hot noodles or rice.

title: meat balls
directions: Put tomato juice and water in large pan and bring to boil; keep boiling.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop the corn and keep warm.
Mix first 3 ingredients and cook to soft ball stage.
Flavor with vanilla.
Mix with corn and shape into balls (grease hands first).
Makes about 50.

title: pork, onion and pepper
directions: Place picnic ham in a large pot, cover with cold water. Cut up 1 large onion in pot, add bay leaf, 2 cloves garlic and one green pepper
(cut
up).	Boil
until
done, about 1 hour. Remove from heat and
let
cool.
Trim	away all lean meat and cut in 1-inch pieces.
In
saucepan heat a little oil.
Put in 3 large onions (cut
up)
and
2 large peppers.
Saute until a little brown, stir in
meat
and
spaghetti sauce.
Mix well. Cook about 10 minutes. Serve with hot rice or bread.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: one dish burrito casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 11 baking pan with non sick spray.
Combine rice and salsa. Spread in the prepared pan.
Arrange burritos evenly over the rice mixture.
Top with chilies, sprinkle with shredded cheese and garnish with sliced olives.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.
Can serve with sour cream and extra salsa.

title: pork chops with mushrooms
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in oil.
Add cream of mushroom soup and water.
Mix together and then add pork chops.
Cover and simmer over low heat for approximately 40 minutes or until pork chops are tender.
Serve with boiled rice and broccoli florets.

title: birdies in the nest
directions: Using a small juice glass or cookie cutter, cut a hole in the center of each slice of bread.
(Save these for bread crumbs or feed the birds.)
Melt 1 tablespoon of margarine in a large skillet on medium low.
Place 3 slices of bread in skillet.
Crack an egg and place it in the hole in one of the slices of bread.
Repeat with other two slices.
Cook for about 1 to 2 minutes and then flip slices with spatula.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes more.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Stir by hand; mix well. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet corn bake
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in rice, tomatoes, corn, salt and pepper sauce.
Mix.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine crumbs and margarine; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crescent roll hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, add tomato sauce, spices and simmer.
Put in casserole dish, sprinkle cheese on top.
Divide crescent rolls and spread sour cream on each.
Roll into a crescent and place on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: betty's apple cake
directions: Cream first four ingredients together.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift together 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter until soft.
Beat in sugar, egg, vanilla and cream.
Stir in flour mixture.
Gradually add the remaining flour until the dough is just stiff enough to roll.
Chill thoroughly.
Place on lightly floured board and roll 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with a floured cutter as desired.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Put in moderate oven (375° to 400°) for 8 to 10 minutes.
I put a cup of walnuts or pecans in my dough.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, mushroom soup, milk and 1/2 can of fried onions.
Place in glass baking dish.
Bake on High for 10 minutes in microwave.
Remove from oven; top with the fried onions left. Return to microwave for about 3 minutes on High.
Or, bake in the oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low calorie dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and stir well.
Chill 2 hours.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into dish.
Let chill at least 4 hours or overnight before serving.

title: fettucini
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Place casserole dish in a preheated 250° oven for 10 minutes.
Place noodles in warmed casserole dish.
Beat together the softened butter and whipping cream until thick. Add parsley and Parmesan cheese; blend well.
Pour over hot noodles.
Return to oven for 2 minutes longer. Toss gently; serve immediately.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Thaw broccoli.
In a bowl, combine egg, broccoli, corn, onion, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in a saucepan; add the stuffing mix. Stir 3/4 cup buttered stuffing mix into broccoli mixture.
Turn into ungreased casserole and sprinkle remaining stuffing mix. Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix melted butter, corn syrup, brown sugar and cinnamon. Spread mixture in bottom of a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts.
Roll sweet roll dough in 48 (1-inch) balls.
Roll each ball in mixture and place in Bundt pan.
Pour any remaining over top.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: frozen pumpkin squares
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger. Add chopped pecans.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with 18 gingersnaps.
Fold pumpkin mixture into ice cream.
Spread 1/2 over gingersnaps.
Cover with the rest of the gingersnaps.
Add remaining ice cream/pumpkin mixture.
Freeze until firm (about 5 hours).
Cut into squares.
Garnish with whipped cream and pecan halves.

title: chicken dijon
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over high heat, brown sesame seed until toasted and light colored.
Pour sesame seed into a small bowl and mix in honey, sherry, mustard and lemon juice.
Place chicken in a baking dish and pour sauce over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes (boneless) or 40 to 45 minutes (bone-in).
Turn chicken once or baste with sauce several times while baking.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook slowly over medium heat until thickened slightly.
May be stored in refrigerator.
Heat in microwave when ready to use again.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole(can't be beat)
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in flour.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Gradually stir into flour mixture.
Add cream.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add rice, mushrooms, chicken, pimiento, parsley, salt and pepper.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly. Serves 8.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Crust:
Mix melted margarine, cake mix and egg.
Spread into a 10 x 15-inch pan.

title: green beans and chili sauce
directions: Brown bacon and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and heat in oven until bubbly.

title: black bean salad
directions: *May substitute 1 cup fresh corn, cooked.

title: cheese danish
directions: Unroll 1 package of crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and egg yolk.
Beat well. Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Beat.
Pour over rolls.
Unroll 1 package crescent rolls on top.
Beat egg white and 1 teaspoon water slightly.
Pour over rolls and spread evenly.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Empty cake mix and jello into bowl dry.
Beat eggs and add to dry mixture.
Add oil and water.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: reese's pieces oatmeal bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large mixing bowl, beat shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix and make into golf ball size balls.
Bake in greased open pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Place the rice and corn in layers in a 2-quart baking dish with tight fitting lid; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 can of water over top.
Layer the onion, green pepper and hamburger meat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pour another can of tomato sauce and 1/2 can of water on top. Cover the meat with bacon, cut in half.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake about 30 minutes longer until bacon is crisp.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: onion soup
directions: Cook together for 2 hours.

title: nana's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in iron skillet over burner.
Pour in batter (it will form a crust on the bottom).
Place immediately in oven at 425°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: angel ambrosia
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions.
Whip the cream. Slice cake into 1-inch pieces.
In a container that can be covered, layer the cake, pudding and whipped cream.
Top with crushed nuts and coconut.
Cover and put in refrigerator until thoroughly chilled.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until sugar is melted good and hot.
Add peanuts.
Cook until peanuts turn brown and the mixture is also looking a golden brown.
This should be at the hard crack stage.
(The syrup will spin a thread that turns brittle when dropped in cold water.)

title: crock-pot hot dogs
directions: In crock-pot, melt jelly and mustard together on medium heat. Cut each hot dog into 4 pieces.
Once jelly and mustard are blended, add hot dogs and cook for 20 minutes before serving. Serve hot dogs hot; leave crock-pot on low heat.
Yield: 20 servings.

title: chicken and cheese marinara
directions: Dip chicken halves in eggs.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in half butter and half olive oil.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Slice cake across to make two layers.
Place one layer in the bottom of the punch bowl.
Punch holes in the cake with the handle of a wooden spoon.
Add crushed pineapple with juice.
Add sliced bananas.
Layer on 1/2 of pudding.
Add second layer of cake, then strawberries, then remaining pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Separate chicken wings at joints into 3 parts each, discarding tips.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Place sherry mixture in medium bowl or plastic bag.
Add chicken.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, stirring once or twice during marinating time.
Drain chicken.
Arrange on double layer of paper toweling around outer edge of carousel or on roasting rack.
Microwave at Medium-high (70%) until juices run clear, 18 to 22 minutes.
If using oven other than Sharpe carousel, rearrange wings twice during cooking time.

title: tex-mex beans with cornmeal dumplings
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, cornmeal, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine egg white, milk and oil; set aside.

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: Cover baking dish with layer of marinara sauce.
Add layer of lasagna, then a layer of spinach.
Top with layer of zucchini and dollops of Ricotta cheese.
Next, add Mozzarella cheese slices and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Spoon marinara sauce over everything.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 9-inch deep dish.
Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl; pour into pan.
Combine remaining ingredients, except 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, in a small bowl.
Spoon within 1 inch of edge of batter, then sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over cream cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and soda, then add other ingredients. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour in a tube pan, greased and floured.

title: potato sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Combine soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
In greased casserole, layer 1/2 of potatoes, soup mix and sausage.
Repeat, ending with sausage.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: medium white sauce
directions: In a 2-cup glass measure, micro-melt the butter 30 to 40 seconds.
With rubber scraper, blend in flour, salt and pepper; stir in milk until well blended.
Microcook, uncovered, 1 minute; stir.
Microcook until thickened and bubbly, 2 to 3 minutes; stir thoroughly every 30 seconds, scraping bottom and sides of cup to remove all lumps.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar and syrup in a pan on medium heat. Bring to a boil, stirring continuously.
After it starts to boil, stop stirring; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour over popped popcorn in a large baking pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 15 minutes.
Mix up and cook 15 more minutes. Cool.

title: barbecue sweet corn
directions: Choose tender, sweet corn in husks. Strip husks down to the end, but do not tear off. Remove the silk. Let corn stand in ice water for 20 minutes. Drain well. Brush corn with butter or margarine and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bring husks up around corn. Be sure entire corn is covered. Wrap each in heavy-duty foil. Barbecue for 15 minutes on each side.
(Very good.)
Now barbecue your ribs.

title: colorful vegetable curry
directions: Salt eggplant cubes and let stand for 30 minutes. In medium saucepan, saute onion with spices for 3-5 minutes. Rinse eggplant and add to onion along with apple juice and water; cover. In another pot, cook spinach until just wilted and chop when it cools a bit to handle comfortably. Add red bell pepper to eggplant mixture and cook about 5 minutes. Add spinach, lemon juice and salt to taste. Cook to blend flavors (2-3 minutes) until vegetables are tender but not mushy. Serve over cooked rice and sprinkle sunflower seeds or nuts. Add a dollop of yogurt to each serving.

title: meat concern
directions: Simmer celery until tender.
Brown meat in skillet; drain. Cook the noodles; drain.
Add meat with all other ingredients and simmer until well mixed, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Delicious.

title: irma's salsa rojo
directions: Mash all ingredients together, using food processor or blender (on lowest setting).

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop bell peppers and onions coarsely.
Combine with boiling water to cover in bowl.
Let stand for 5 minutes; drain.
Add boiling water to cover.
Let stand for 10 minutes; drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar and salt in saucepan; mix well.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Spoon into 2 sterilized 1-pint jars; seal with 2 piece lids.
Yields 2 pints.

title: hummus
directions: Drain and rinse chickpeas.
Mash peas with a potato masher or ricer and set aside.
Crush garlic and add teaspoon of salt. Combine with lemon juice.
Stir into chickpeas.
Beat in tahini. If mixture is too heavy, add some reserved juice from chickpeas. Can be made in food processor.
Chill after garnishing with parsley.
Serve with pita bread and raw vegetables.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain and arrange fruit in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter. Add sugar and curry. Mix thoroughly in small pan.
Add this mixture to fruit.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
After it has cooked awhile, push the "goodie" (sugar mixture) down further in the fruit.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Make pie shell with a high rim.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar and blend well.
Separate egg yolks from whites.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add lemon rind and juice, flour and salt; mix well.
Stir in milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold into lemon mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 35 minutes.
Serve cold. Makes 1 pie.

title: busy day cobbler
directions: Place fruit in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and water and pour over fruit.
Mix egg, salt, baking powder, sugar and flour together.
Spread over fruit.
Pour butter over top. Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mom's pea casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef; drain fat.
In casserole dish, layer 1 can peas, 1/2 ground beef, 1/2 amount of cheese and 1/2 amount of cracker crumbs.
Repeat with 2nd can of peas, beef and cheese; add milk, then cracker crumbs.
Mix mix top layer of crumbs with a little melted margarine.
Bake about 45 minutes.
Let set before serving.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat until melted in double boiler.
Serve in chafing dish with crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place rice on bottom of casserole dish.
In mixing bowl, blend soups and water.
Pour over rice and place chicken in.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: deviled macaroni(in honor of broodmare, "clara w.")
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water, according to package directions; drain.
Combine soups, milk and deviled ham; stir in cooked macaroni; mix lightly.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with mixture of corn flakes and cheese.
Bake in a 375°
oven for 30 minutes, or until browned and bubbly.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, vanilla and butter in saucepan.
Mix well. Boil mixture on high heat 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour at once into a greased 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: cracker snacks
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over box of oyster crackers.
Put on lid and shake container to mix.
Let stand overnight.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Melt oleo and cheese together.
Add sour cream.
Mix together with potatoes.
Layer potatoes in baking dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Continue with layers of potatoes and cheese, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pot roast in foil
directions: Do not add salt.
Place foil in 30 x 18-inch baking pan. Place meat in pan.
Mix soup and onion soup mix.
Spread over meat.
Add vegetables.
Sprinkle with water.
Fold over and seal. Bake at 300° for 3 to 4 hours.
Skim fat from gravy.
Serve gravy with meat.
Serve with a salad and bread.

title: eileen's barbecue shrimp
directions: Layer the shrimp not too thinly in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 to 1 bottle barbecue seasoning.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add sticks of butter on top.
The more butter, the more gravy to dip your French bread in. Yum, Yum.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325° to 350°, until done. Shrimp should turn pink.
When done, dip French bread in gravy and enjoy.

title: super duper potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in their jackets until tender (better to undercook than to overcook).
Put into refrigerator and chill for 24 hours.
Warm in saucepan the margarine, half and half and salt. Peel potatoes and grate into large bowl.
Pour half and half mixture over potatoes; add cheese.
Mix together and put into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: bean relish
directions: Drain beans.
Cut onions and tops and pepper.
Mix dressing and pour over beans in a wide, flat container.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Keeps well.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In a 2 quart glass casserole dish, blend together sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in boiling water, then microwave 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes, stirring about every minute until thickened and translucent.
In medium bowl beat egg yolks lightly, then gradually stir first mixture into egg yolks, blending well.
Microwave at medium high (70 percent power) 2 minutes.
(Less than 2 minutes if mixture is thick).
Cool the mixture; then add the butter and fresh lemon juice and lemon peel.
Pour the cooled mixture into a cool pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped meringue.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and roll into one-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pork chop cacciatore
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops.
Season with salt and pepper; place on baking sheet.
Top with slices of onion.
Combine sauce, tomatoes and brown sugar in bowl.
Pour over pork chops.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover; top each chop with green pepper ring.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: miami fling
directions: Combine the
juice
concentrate,
water, apricot nectar and carbonated beverage.
To
serve, pour over ice in glasses. Garnish with orange slices.
To carry on a picnic, pour juices and water in a container
with lid and add carbonated beverage just before serving at picnic.
Serves 6.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Variations:
Red and green peppers, chopped onion or pimento.

title: cheese balls
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Combine with other ingredients except pecans and mix well.
Chill slightly (can be handled easier).
Form into a ball or a loaf.
Put pecans on waxed paper.
Roll ball or loaf in pecans.
Wrap and refrigerate.

title: delicious coconut cream pie
directions: Mix cream of coconut with milk.
Add marshmallows.
Cook over low heat until marshmallows melt.
Cool in bowl and refrigerate 1 hour or until mixture starts to jell.
Beat jelled mixture with electric mixer until frothy.
Carefully fold in whipped cream. Blend in 2 cups of coconut by hand.
Pour into pie shells, dividing evenly.
Sprinkle remaining coconut over pies and refrigerate at least 6 hours before serving.

title: g~g's goetta
directions: Place meats and onions in a pan with enough water to cover. Squeeze meat until fine; add a pinch of salt. Fill a spice basket or a small tea ball, half full with pickling spice and peeled, halved garlic. Put basket under water and meat. Stir when meat boils, add bouillon cubes, stir. Wait 1/2 hour and add oats gradually; keep stirring until oats are done, (about 10 minutes). Pour into shallow pans and let cool, refrigerate. Slice thin and fry until crispy. Catsup is good on top.

title: butter chews
directions: Cream butter and sugar; blend in flour.
Pat into bottom of a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
In a bowl, beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
Beat egg yolks until thick; add brown sugar and beat well.
Stir in nuts and coconut; fold in egg whites and spread over baked crust.
Return to oven and bake 25 or 30 minutes longer.
Remove from oven, cool in pan, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put pulled chicken into broth with chopped eggs, celery, drained peas, drained chopped pimentos, salt and pepper to taste. Add flour and water; put in large dish.
Place crust over and bake at 450° until crust is brown.

title: fried okra and green tomatoes
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Add cornmeal and toss gently.
Pour oil to depth of 2 inches into a large skillet (or use Fry Daddy).
Heat oil.
Fry half of mixture until golden brown.
Remove with slotted spoon and drain.
Repeat procedure. Sprinkle with salt and serve.

title: dunking cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Cream all wet ingredients. Add mixtures together.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
May add nuts and raisins if you wish.

title: noodle mousse
directions: Make cream sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Add cheese, noodles and egg yolks.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into mold (jello or Bundt cake) that has been sprayed with Pam.
Place a piece of brown paper (sack) on top of mold while baking.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: french bread toast casserole
directions: Melt butter, sugar and maple syrup in microwave or on stove top.
Pour in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place sliced apples on top of mixture pan. Cover with bread slices.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Grease a 9x13 inch casserole dish. Drain oysters, reserving juice. In a small mixing bowl combine butter and crushed saltine crackers. Cut the oysters into small pieces, set aside. In a small mixing bowl combine cream, oyster juice and Worcestershire sauce. Spread one can of corn onto bottom of casserole dish. Layer 1/2 of the oysters over the corn, 1/2 of the cracker mixture. Repeat layering with remaining ingredients. Pour the oyster juice mixture over the top of the entire casserole. Cover the casserole dish with aluminum foil. Bake casserole for 20 minutes. Remove foil and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: nippersink prune cake
directions: Beat together 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs and oil until well blended.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and 1 teaspoon soda.
Add this to the blended egg mixture alternately with 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Add prunes, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Combine cheese, onion, celery, sour cream, water chestnuts, pimentos, corn, green beans and soup.
Mix well and put in a buttered casserole.
Crumble crackers on top and slice margarine and put on top.
Bake at 300° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans and mushroom soup together.
Add whole can of onions on top.
Cook in large shallow dish in oven (350°) for about 1/2 hour.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together in order.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: oyster stew
directions: Combine onion, potatoes and milk in medium-sized boiler over medium heat.
Bring to a slow boil for a few minutes.
Add oysters, margarine and pepper; bring back to a boil for about 5 minutes (until onion and potato cut through easily).
Remove from heat and serve in bowls with oyster crackers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack firmly into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Bring chicken broth, onion and seasonings to a boil in saucepan.
Add zucchini. Cook for 20 minutes or until zucchini is very tender.
Add peas.
Mix well.
Process in blender until smooth or press through sieve.
Serve hot or cold in serving bowls.

title: ella marie cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Then add raisins and molasses and mix well.
Add flour, spices and sour milk.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: microwaved corn-on-the-cob
directions: Break or cut stem; trim husk to ear.
Remove dark outer husks. Cook 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on High per ear.
Pull back husks. Remove silk.
Butter and salt to taste.

title: tacos
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add garlic, salt and pepper.
Add small amount of water and cook slowly until tender.
Add mashed potatoes and mix well with meat.
Warm tortillas in grease in skillet; remove and place 1 tablespoon of meat mixture on center of tortilla.
Fold over and pin with toothpick.
Fry taco in grease until brown; drain well on paper towel.
Serve with chopped onions, lettuce, canned, peeled green chili peppers and hot sauce.

title: quick strudel
directions: Roll out biscuits.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan or larger if you double recipe.
Cut apples in 1/8.
Place on biscuits, drop pieces of butter on top and pour on syrup as desired.
Sprinkle on raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon juice.
Bake until biscuits are done at 350°.
Eat warm and enjoy.
If desired, top with whip cream, lemon sauce or ice cream.

title: strawberry banana dessert
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix. Beat well. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in whipped topping, then strawberries and bananas. Line side and bottom of 3 1/2-quart glass serving bowl with cake slice. Spoon pudding mixture into prepared bowl. Cover. Chill. Garnish with additional strawberries and banana slices. Refrigerate leftovers if any is left.

title: bacon-cheese biscuits
directions: Combine flour and sugar; cut in shortening with pastry blender until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Set aside.

title: peppered-parmesan spoonbread
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Grease a deep 2-quart baking dish. In large saucepan, gradually stir cornmeal into boiling water; cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes until consistency of mush. Stir in butter, sugar and cheese; stir to blend. Stir in milk, egg yolks and pepper. Blend thoroughly. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; fold into corn meal mixture. Pour into baking dish. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lowered fat fudge cake
directions: Heat chocolate with water over very low heat, stirring until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup sugar; cook and stir 2 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat with a mixer on high speed for 5 minutes the eggs. Gradually add sugar.
Stir in pumpkin pie filling and lemon juice. Add flour, baling powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt. Spread in a greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with nuts.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Starting at narrow end, roll towel and cake together.
Cool.
Unroll.
Spread filling on top.

title: orange delight
directions: Gently fold cottage cheese, crushed pineapple and dry gelatin into prepared topping.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Spoon into individual serving dishes and garnish each serving with strawberry slices and mint, if desired.
Each serving:
3/4 cup.
Per serving:
78 calories, 1 milk exchange.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Mix chicken with mushroom soup and tomato soup.
Fill soup can with milk one time.
Add milk.
Brown slightly onion and celery. Add.
Cook noodles and drain.
Layer noodles and chicken mixture alternately.
Cover top with grated cheese.
Cook at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Heat vinegar and water.
Put eggs, onions, bay leaves and salt in a large mouth jar.
Pour vinegar over eggs, etc.
Put top on jar.
Takes from 1 to 2 weeks to pickle.

title: yankee french toast
directions: Whip eggs, milk and vanilla in flat bottom bowl. Fold in cinnamon. Dip both sides of bread in egg mixture and cook in a non-stick pan until golden brown on both sides. Serve with favorite topping.

title: letty's aerobic brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup of milk.
Press half of mixture in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
While cake mixture bakes, soften caramels in saucepan with 1/2 cup milk over low heat.
Remove cake mixture from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Pour/spread caramel mixture on top of chips.
Crumble remaining cake mixture over all and bake for 16 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and refrigerate for 1 hour before cutting into squares.
Enjoy!
Then go to your aerobics class every day for the next two weeks to work off the calories!

title: macaroni
directions: Mix mayonnaise and milk in a small bowl.
Cook macaroni just like the directions say.
After you cook it, wash it.
Then cut your onions up in the macaroni and leave it in a covered bowl until you get ready for the rest of the ingredients.
Then cut up your eggs, pepper, ham and relish.
Then mix it all up.

title: sourdough bread
directions: To Feed:
Every few days, add 1 cup warm water, 3/4 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons mashed potato powder.
Let sit out 8 hours, lightly covered, then refrigerate.

title: cauliflower cheese soup
directions: In saucepan, heat first 4 ingredients until carrots are tender.
Stir in soup, milk, corn and cauliflower; heat through. Just before serving, stir in cheeses and pepper.

title: scalloped potatoes with pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in hot oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Place chopped potatoes and onions into large pot; cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Add vegetables (except corn), chopping tomatoes.
Add desired seasonings and chicken broth.
Simmer over low heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add corn 10 minutes before end of cooking time to thicken.
Stir often to prevent sticking. Serve hot with fresh corn bread.
Makes about 3 quarts.
Freezes well.

title: layered strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add fruit and chill until partially set, then put half of mixture in a mold and place in refrigerator until completely set.
Cover with sour cream.
Spoon on second half of partially set gelatin.
Refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce; garnish with grapes and tangerine petals.
(To double, use 2 and 1/2 quart dish; fix above mixture for the bottom, let set, then fix another mixture for the bottom; let set, then fix another mixture for the top, and use 12 ounces sour cream.)

title: buttermilk yeast buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Stir to dissolve with buttermilk and sugar.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Add warm butter and eggs; mix.
Sift soda and salt with 4 cups flour. Add to liquid mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour until dough is no longer sticky.
Knead well on floured board. Oil large bowl.
Place dough in bowl and let rise until doubled. Knead again.
Pinch off dough size of egg.
Bake in 400° oven until brown.
Brush with melted butter while still warm.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Dice and boil carrots in salt water until tender.
Drain and cool.
Alternate or mix together layers of carrots, pepper rings and onion rings in container.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep a week under refrigeration and is better if make several days ahead and allowed to marinate before serving.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix well.
Chill for two hours before serving.

title: daddy's favorite cookie
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Dip in sugar.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Heat sour cream to lukewarm in a large saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar, soda, salt and yeast (crumbled).
Mix well.
Turn dough onto floured board and fold over several times until it is smooth.
Roll into an oblong 24 x 6-inches.
Spread with 2 tablespoons of soft butter.
Sprinkle half of dough with mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon.
Fold over the other half. Cut into 24 strips, 1-inch wide, and twist.
Cover and let rise until light (1 hour).
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Add 1 cup hot water to Jell-O and cream cheese.
Let melt.
Use mixer to beat cheese.
Add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: strawberry brownie torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Line with wax paper, extended up sides of pans.
Grease wax paper.
Prepare brownie mix according to directions on box.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 20 minutes or until top springs back when touched.
Let cool.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Steam squash until well done.
Mash fine. Chop onion fine. Saute in margarine until tender.
Mix all ingredients together. Chill until very cold. Form in oblong croquettes and roll in soft bread crumbs. Cook in deep fat until brown.

title: rice
directions: Cook rice in 2 1/2 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Saute onion 5 minutes in butter.
Remove from heat; add hot rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, bay leaf, salt and pepper; toss.
Layer half rice mixture, chilies and grated cheese; repeat and sprinkle with parsley.

title: taco salad dip
directions: In small bowl microwave cream cheese for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes on High to soften.
In medium serving bowl combine salsa, sour cream and cream cheese.
Stir well.
Top with layer of scallions, layer of lettuce, layer of green pepper, layer of tomatoes and layer of cheese.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Mix just before serving.

title: flank steak teriyaki
directions: Mix marinade ingredients and pour over meat.
Let stand 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat 7 minutes, brushing once with marinade.
Turn and broil 5 to 7 minutes longer, brushing once more.
Add pineapple slices for the last 3 to 4 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill 8 hours, serve with slotted spoon.
Serves 10.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Butter 1 1/2-quart oblong baking dish.
Arrange fruit in dish. Mix together dry ingredients.
Beat large egg with a fork.
Add milk, vanilla and melted oleo.
Stir in dry ingredients and spread over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry and drain sausage.
Alternate layers of bread, sausage and cheese in buttered casserole dish.
Mix together eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over layers and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Roll chicken in flour and lightly brown chicken in 2 tablespoons oil.
Set aside.
Stir-fry vegetables in 2 tablespoons of oil until tender.
Mix together; add soy sauce and salt and pepper to taste.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and put in buttered casserole dish. Top with crushed crackers which have been mixed with butter. Bake at 350° until top is brown.

title: butterscotch chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, vanilla, shortening and about half of the cake mix (dry) until light and fluffy.
Stir in remaining cake mix, the butterscotch chips and nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoon, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes (cookies will be soft in centers when done).
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Mix in vanilla and water. Add flour and pecans; blend well. Chill until firm (1 to 2 hours).
Shape into crescents and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° about 20 minutes or until edges are pale brown. Cool slightly; roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix and bake cornbread as directed on package.
When cooled completely, crumble very fine.
Mix all other ingredients into cornbread.

title: baked corn
directions: Preheat oven
to 350°.	Melt butter in medium saucepan. Stir in sugar and flour until well blended.
Remove from heat. Add milk, eggs and baking powder.
Mix well.
Fold into thawed corn. Bake for 1 hour in a 2 quart buttered casserole dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; save broth.
Pull chicken apart and mix with chicken soup and celery soup.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix stuffing, oleo and 1 cup broth.
Place
on top of chicken mixture. Bake at 300° until bubbly.
Better if made and set in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight before cooking.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly. Cook about 12 minutes or until a soft ball forms when dropped in a cup of cold water.
Remove from heat.
Dump in margarine and cocoa. Stir until mixed.
Dump in marshmallows and beat until it starts to get thick.
Add pecans.
Pour in buttered dish or pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Beat the egg; add sugar and chocolate syrup.
Sift the flour, baking soda, and salt together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Then fold in butter and nuts.
Spread in a well greased 9 inch square pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 16 brownies.

title: sticky buns
directions: Heat mixture and pour over dough balls.

title: easy chili
directions: Melt bacon fat in frying pan and add beef, salt, pepper and onion.
Cook about 5 minutes or until beef is well browned.
Add tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes, pea beans and chili powder.
Simmer until mixture reaches desired thickness.

title: pink salad or dessert
directions: Put the strawberry jello into a 2-quart dish.
Put pineapple and juice in a pot and let it come to a boil.
Pour over the jello, then let stand until it becomes lukewarm.
Blend while you are waiting for it to cool.
It will curdle if not lukewarm.
Next, blend in the Cool Whip and then the cottage cheese.
Use fresh cottage cheese.
This will serve 8 to 10 and will keep about 10 days.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken.
Take meat off bones.
Cook 3/4 stick margarine with 6 tablespoons of flour.
Add 3 cups chicken broth.
Let cool a few minutes, then add chicken.
Pour into a baking dish.
Put sliced eggs on top.
Top with biscuits, divided.
Cook at 400° until biscuits are brown.

title: hot antipasto hors d'oeuvres
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with 1 roll of crescent rolls.
Layer meat and cheese in order as written.
Top with sliced peppers.
Pour most of egg mixture over layers.
Top with other large crescent roll layer.
Brush top with remaining egg mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake 10 minutes or until brown.
Cut in squares and serve warm or room temperature.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Simmer squash and tomatoes until tender.
Add onion which has been sauteed in the butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into bake dish; top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: aunt tina's apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix 2 cups flour, salt and baking powder together; cut in lard.
Add milk, a little at a time (should look similar to bread dough).
Roll out or spread on large cookie sheet.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat eggs; stir in bananas, oil and water.
Add to flour mixture; stir until moistened.
Stir in cereal.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake 55 to 65 minutes at 350°.

title: vidalia onion rings
directions: Peel onions, cut into 1/2-inch slices and separate into rings. Place in a large Ziploc bag (or paper sack) with 1 cup flour. Shake until rings are coated.

title: pink devil's sandwich spread
directions: Blend.
Let set in refrigerator for better flavor.

title: spanish lima beans
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper in butter for 5 minutes.
Combine with the other ingredients and place in a casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine.
Cook broccoli 5 minutes in box in microwave.
Add cream of chicken soup and milk.
Add a little more milk if you prefer it thinner.
Add broccoli and 1/3 box Velveeta cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve with bowl of fresh fruits (apples, pears, grapes, bananas, etc.) and crackers.

title: creamy deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove yolks; mash.
Blend in cream cheese, relish and seasonings, mixing until well blended.
Refill whites.

title: herb pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Drain olives, blot dry on paper towel.
Sprinkle equal amounts remaining ingredients on top of cream cheese.
Roll tortillas tightly.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut rolls into inch pieces.
Discard ends. Serve with spirals facing up.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat in top of double boiler until cheese is melted.
Do not overheat.
Do not dilute with water.
Serve with bread sticks, crackers, Melba toast, vegies or whatever suits your fancy.

title: creole franks
directions: Cook bacon but not crisp.
Add chopped onion and cook until tender but not brown.
Stir in pineapple juice, catsup and chili powder.
Score franks diagonally at 1-inch intervals.
Add to the sauce.
Cover and bring to a boil; add pepper and simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve on fluffy hot rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable dip (1)
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.	Best if mixed approx. 6 hours before serving.

title: chicken liver scramble
directions: Cook chicken livers, onion and celery in butter until vegetables are tender but not brown.
Remove chicken livers and dice; return to skillet.
Mix eggs and seasonings together and pour over liver and onion mixture.
Add cream cheese.
As eggs begin to set, draw turner across bottom to form large soft curds. Cook until eggs are thick but still moist.
Makes 4 servings.

title: julie's favorite butterscotch dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix together flour and oleo until like pie crust.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: venison chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut steaks diagonally across the grain into thin slices, then cut strips about 2 inches long.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Place garlic clove in hot oil.
Remove after 3 minutes. Add meat to oil.
Cook over medium heat, turning as needed, until browned.
Mix in onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and ginger. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until just tender, about 3 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with stock and soy sauce.
Stir into mixture in skillet.
Bring to boil and cook, stirring constantly, until liquid is thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: reese's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix graham crackers and margarine.
Pat into pie pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 12 minutes.

title: creamy chicken and vegetables with savory biscuits(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, thyme, black pepper and 1/2 cup milk until blended.
Spray small cookie sheet; spoon biscuit batter into 4 mounds about 3 inches apart, spreading each to about a 3-inch round.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: italian chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oleo and Italian dressing.
Place brown chicken in baking dish.
Mix soup with milk.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: water chestnut dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill for 4 hours. Serve with fresh vegetables.
Makes 2 1/4 cups of dip.

title: barbecued zucchini chicken
directions: Cut zucchini into 1/8-inch slices and place in bottom of 1 1/2-quart greased baking pan.
Arrange deboned chicken breasts over zucchini.

title: marshmallow brownies
directions: Beat eggs until thick; add sugar.
Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler (chocolate chips and squares); let cool.
Add vanilla, flour and chocolate to eggs and mix well.
Add marshmallows.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Bring to a full boil and boil 3 minutes:
peppers (chopped up), vinegar and sugar.
Drain and save juice, throwing peppers away. Add to juice the Certo and boil 1 full minute.
Add green food color.
Put in jelly jars topped with paraffin wax.
This is good spread on Philadelphia cream cheese and used as a cracker spread or dip.

title: nancy's barbecue kielbasa
directions: Cook and slice favorite kielbasa.

title: blueberry cream cheese cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package, making 3 cake layers.

title: herb broiled chicken
directions: Arrange chicken bone side up on broiler pan.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend well.
Brush mixture on chicken.
Broil about 4-inches from heat for 8 minutes, brushing frequently with sauce.
Turn chicken; continue broiling, brushing frequently with sauce.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear.
Serve warm or cold.

title: swiss quiche
directions: Sprinkle cheese, onions and ham in pie shell.
Beat eggs, half and half and seasonings.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake on lowest oven rack for 40 minutes.
Done when knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry ham steak
directions: Pour water in frying pan.
Add ham steaks.
Spread jelly on both steaks; add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cover and let simmer for 20 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and vinegar.
Mix together seasonings. Put all beans in bowl with sliced onion.
Pour sugar, oil, vinegar and seasonings over.
Mix gently.
