Place garlic on a toothpick and add to mixture.
Let set overnight.
Mix again to marinate well. Spoon out to serve, with slotted spoon.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain.
Add cheese.
Add eggs, onion and bread crumbs.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake about 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: hot salsa(fresh)
directions: Chop all ingredients very fine and add lime juice.
Add salt when ready to serve.

title: granny's old time potato salad
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and boil until done.
Drain and mash. Add butter,
mustard,
pickles,
onions and mayonnaise. Stir up well and
add
eggs.
Garnish
with
quartered,
hard-boiled eggs and sliced red bell peppers.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix and beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until smooth. Add zucchini.
Sift
dry
ingredients;	add
nuts
and	fruit. Combine all
ingredients.
Grease
and
flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325°
for 45 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: creole shrimp and rice
directions: Melt butter in a heavy skillet; add onions, green pepper and celery.
Brown lightly.
Add sage, salt and tomato juice and bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve on steamed rice.
Serves 4.

title: tomato corn salad
directions: In a large salad bowl combine the corn, tomatoes, celery, cucumber, green pepper and onion.
In a small bowl combine the remaining ingredients.
Gently blend into the salad.

title: basic filling for cream pies
directions: Cook until thickened all, except butter.
Add butter.
Add bananas to crust or add coconut to mixture.

title: apple bars
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until light colored.
Add flour, which has been sifted together with cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Add oil and vanilla; fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: chocolate mayo cake
directions: Mix together everything except mayo.
Fold in mayo.
Fold into pan (2 layers).
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: 4th of july flag cake
directions: You will need a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Mix with sugar, coconut and nuts.
In another bowl mix butter, eggs and milk.
Combine ingredients together. Bake in greased and waxed tube pan for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 275°.

title: apple something
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs slightly and add sugar.
Mix well.
Peel apples and dice.
Add all other ingredients together.
Grease and flour a cake pan.
Put mixture in pan and top with sprinkles of sugar.
(I usually use cinnamon and sugar mixed for the top.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat soup and cheese in saucepan over low heat until cheese melts.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into mold.
Chill overnight.
Tastes best when prepared 24 hours in advance of serving.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Separate egg yolks and beat egg whites separately in a bowl. Cream butter and egg yolks.
Sift flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with sour cream.
Add vanilla, then fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: baked carrot and apple casserole
directions: Place layer of apples in 11 x 7-inch baking dish, alternating with carrots until all are used.
Mix sugar with flour and sprinkle over vegetables. Mix cornstarch with juice and pour over dish.
Crumble brown sugar and pecans over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: paul's veggie dish(a.k.a. cadillac stew)
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Toss with butter, garlic and oregano and put in bottom of a large casserole.

title: garlic oyster crackers
directions: Mix together, except crackers.
Add crackers and stir until oil is absorbed.
You may have to let them stand a few minutes.

title: oven kalua pork
directions: Place pork fat side up in roasting pan or deep casserole. Combine water and liquid smoke and pour over meat.
Sprinkle with Hawaiian salt.
Cover and roast at 400° for 3 hours.
Remove from pan; discard the fat and shred the meat.

title: old fashioned butter cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cream butter; gradually beat in sugar.
Cream well.
Stir in egg, cream and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients gradually.
Mix well.
Chill if necessary.
Roll, 1/3 at a time, 1/8 inch thick on floured surface.
Cut to desired shapes.
Bake on ungreased sheets at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes until light golden brown.
Decorate.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Good for dipping celery, cauliflower, carrots, etc.

title: ham and green bean casserole
directions: Combine soup, beans, ham and pepper.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Microwave for 6 minutes on High or until hot.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Microwave 2 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli amandine
directions: Remove large leaves and tough part of stalks from broccoli. Separate flowerets; cut stalks into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add broccoli to small amount of boiling water in medium saucepan; cover. Reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain.

title: pineapple carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line muffin tins with paper baking cups.
In large bowl, combine and thoroughly mix all dry ingredients.
In small bowl, combine oil, pineapple and egg; blend well.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in carrots, raisins and walnuts.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 22 minutes.
Makes 16 muffins.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine; mix together and press into pan.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top
evenly with remaining ingredients; press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.
Makes 24 bars.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain fruit and mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; cool.
Beat softened cream cheese with electric mixer until lumps are out.
Add cooled gelatin to cream cheese and beat in.
Add crushed pineapple and juice.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Refrigerate.
Allow to set 2 or 3 hours.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Chop shrimp, set aside.
Melt margarine or oil and add onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic in heavy pot.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat until onions wilt.
Add tomato paste, stirring constantly, 15 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups water and season. Add sugar and continue to cook 40 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until oil floats to the top.
Add shrimp and continue cooking and stirring another 20 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/2 cup water.
Add and cook another 5 minutes.
Mix with cooked rice, add green onion tops and parsley.
Mix again.
Serves 8.
Excellent.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine hash browns, cream of chicken soup, sour cream, cheese, 1/2 cup melted butter, salt and onion.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine frosted flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: italian meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat 2 eggs with a fork.
Add 1 1/2 pounds ground beef, bread crumbs, green pepper, 2 teaspoons salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Mix together.
Press evenly into a 9-inch pie pan to make the "crust" or "shell".
In a bowl, combine mushrooms and 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese, tomato paste and oregano.
Add 2/3 cup water; mix.
Pour into "shell" and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Arrange mashed potatoes over tomato mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake until cheese melts. Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut the "pie" into 6 wedges.
Serves 6.

title: baked ziti
directions: In large skillet, heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add beef, onion and garlic; stir frequently.
Cook 3 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce and oregano; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.

title: spaghetti with herbed tomatoes and cheese
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Over medium heat in hot oil, cook garlic until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, basil and salt, stirring until hot.
Drain spaghetti; toss gently with tomato mixture, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a bowl.
Pour into two greased pie plates.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until brown.
This coconut pie makes its own crust.

title: amish lemon bars
directions: Cream together and press in a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: Cook noodles as directed. Stir together sour cream, 1/4 cup cheese, chives, salt, pepper and garlic.
Return drained noodles to kettle and stir in butter. Fold in sour cream mixture. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese.

title: coconut trifle
directions: Place cake cubes in a large bowl. In a bowl, whisk milk and pudding mixes for 2 minutes. Let stand for 2 minutes or until soft-set. Stir in ice cream until well mixed. Pour over cake cubes; stir just until combined. Transfer to a 5-quart trifle bowl. Spread with whipped topping and sprinkle with coconut. Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: apricot delight jello salad
directions: Mix jello as directed on box, allowing to partially set.
Add drained pineapple and bananas to jello saving pineapple juice. Combine eggs, flour and sugar with pineapple juice and cook until thick.
Add cream cheese and let cool.
Prepare 2 small packages of Dream Whip as directed on package.
Add to the cooled cream cheese mixture and pour over salad.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add sour cream, soda and flavorings.
Next, add eggs 2 at a time with 1 cup of the flour until all eggs and flour have been added.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. May be served plain or glazed.

title: hot cheesy seafood dip
directions: Combine jalapeno process cheese, cream cheese and margarine in top of double boiler.
Bring water to boil and reduce heat to low. Cook, stirring frequently, until cheese melts.
Stir in shrimp or crab meat and green chilies.
Put mixture in chafing dish and sprinkle with onion tops.
Serve warm with tortilla chips or your favorite crackers.
Yields 4 cups.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk to dry ingredients.
Turn dough out onto floured surface and lightly knead.
Refrigerate dough until needed.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into rounds with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Heat corn syrup to quite hot, but do not boil.
Mix with coconut.
Set aside 1 hour.
Dampen hands and roll into small balls.
Keep hands dampened for easy handling.
Let balls set for awhile, then dip in your favorite coating.

title: scalloped potatoes and hot dogs
directions: Place potatoes, onion and enough water to cover in a large saucepan; cook until tender.
Melt margarine in another pan.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add cheese; cook and stir until cheese melts and sauce is thickened. Add hot dogs; heat through.
Drain potatoes; place in a bake dish. Add hot dogs and sauce; mix lightly.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pan toasted garlic bread
directions: In
skillet,
melt
butter.
Stir in pepper and garlic. Dip both sides of bread in butter, then cook over medium heat, watching
closely until bread is lightly browned.
Reduce heat to low
and
turn bread over; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and continue cooking until cheese is melted, about 1 to 2 minutes. Serve immediately.	Great with lasagna or spaghetti.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs; stir in oats, flour, soda and chips. Bake on greased cookie sheets for 12 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: french-style green beans
directions: Cook minced onion in margarine.
Remove from stove.
Add beans, grated cheese, bacon, almonds and mushroom soup.
Mix thoroughly and put into casserole.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers on top. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine vegetables, butter and Cheez Whiz in bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Prepare apples	and set aside.	Measure salad oil (room temperature) into
mixing bowl.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix well at low
speed until creamy smooth. Add flour in small amounts. Add salt,
cinnamon
and
vanilla.
When batter is well mixed, add apples and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Combine water and raisins
and boil for 5 minutes.
Cool. Cream butter and sugar, add eggs and ; beat well.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts to cooled raisin mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda salt and spices.
Add to raisin mixture and blend.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in hot 350 degrees oven for 15 minutes.
Yields:
60 cookies.

title: holly berry wreaths
directions: Melt marshmallows and margarine in top of double boiler. Remove from heat and add food coloring.
Add cornflakes and mix well until all flakes are well coated.
Drop quickly by teaspoonful on buttered wax paper.
Form into wreaths with buttered fingers. Decorate with cinnamon drops while still warm.

title: easy sweet rolls
directions: Melt oleo.
Add brown sugar and milk.
Add dry pudding mix. Cut or break 2 loaves of frozen dough into pieces.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan and pour mix over it.
Let rise to double.
Add cinnamon, nuts or raisins, if desired.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar and oil in large bowl.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Set aside.
Add dry ingredients alternately with water. Add pumpkin.
Add dates, pecans, or both at this time.
Pour into three well greased and floured 9-inch x 5-inch x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake in preheated 325° oven for one hour, or until they test done.
Remove from pans when barely warm.

title: glazed chicken and vegetables
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Skewer neck skin to back.
Tie legs to tail.
Twist wing tips under back.
Place, breast side up, on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Brush with oil.
Roast chicken, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: sausage bake
directions: Butter a 13 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Spread dough on bottom.
Press seams together to seaL.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over sausage and cheese.
Cook at 425° for 15 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: red punch
directions: Prepare first 2 ingredients and put in ring mold and freeze. Put all Hawaiian Punch into punch bowl and add the remaining ingredients listed.
Place frozen mold in punch bowl to float.

title: mama's tomato catsup
directions: Wash and slice all vegetables; combine tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Let stand about 30 minutes.
Add vinegar, sugar and spices, tied in a square of cloth.
Boil gently until thick, stirring often.
If you put vegetable slices through a coarse sieve before adding vinegar, catsup will be much smoother textured.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Makes 4 pints.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Drain and add tomato sauce, taco mix, water and chili powder.
Simmer for 5 minutes. In separate bowl, mix sour cream and eggs.
Layer in pan alternating meat mixture, sour cream mixture, cheese and chips. Put remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: stroganoff meatballs on parsley buttered noodles
directions: Combine the ground beef, rolled oats, egg, catsup, onion and salt.
Mix thoroughly and shape into 24 one-inch balls.
Place in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish and bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes or until done.
While meatballs bake, cook noodles, uncovered, in a large amount of boiling water for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain thoroughly.
Melt butter in same pan, add cooked noodles with parsley or Italian seasoning and dill weed.
Toss to coat noodles, cover and keep warm.

title: crab-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms with damp towels.
Remove stems and reserve for other uses.
Combine mushroom caps and Italian dressing; cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Drain well.
Combine 1/2 cup bread crumbs and remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Spoon crabmeat mixture into mushroom caps and sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
Place in a large baking dish and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper, parsley and garlic in shortening, until tender.
Chop eggplant pulp.
Add tomatoes, seasonings, water and eggplant to mixture.
Cover and simmer until eggplant is tender. Remove bay leaves.
Add shrimp.
Combine butter and bread crumbs. When putting eggplant mixture in casserole dish, add a little of the bread crumbs.
Top casserole with rest
of crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pound cake or jelly cake
directions: Bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until tester comes out clean.

title: chocolate snack cake
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
In another bowl, combine water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients and mix just until blended.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan (use two pans, 13 x 9-inches).
Mix all ingredients; spread in pans.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 to 35 minutes.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces; serve hot or cold.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Make crescents according to directions.
Flatten out in jelly roll pan. Bake until lightly golden color. Cool completely. Cream together the next 6 ingredients. Spread over crust. Add vegetable toppings.

title: baked fudge
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs, cocoa, flour, vanilla and pecans. Pour into a 9 x 11-inch glass pan.
Put glass dish inside a large metal cookie sheet that has water in it.
Set timer for 35 minutes and check every 5 minutes until the sides of the fudge begin to crack.
Serve warm or cold.
Great with ice cream or Cool Whip on top!

title: broccoli-onion casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well; set aside.
Cook frozen or fresh onions in boiling salted water about 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain; set aside.
In the same saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour, salt and dash pepper.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.

title: chili con queso(kay-so)
directions: Cube cheese and melt together; after cheese melts, add cream and stir constantly, then add chopped tomato, chilies, onions and garlic.
Stir to blend ingredients; add cream if desired.
Heat for 15 minutes.
Serve in warm dish with Tostitos.

title: chicken florentine(origin:  french)
directions: Pound chicken until thin.
Season to taste.
Cook and drain spinach.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and mix with spinach, cream cheese and vermouth.
In the middle of each chicken breast, spread 1 teaspoon of butter, some Swiss cheese and some spinach mixture. Fold breasts to cover stuffing.
Spread 1 teaspoon of butter on outside of each chicken breast and sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese and a little paprika.
Place in a baking dish with a little water or white wine.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: nannie's chicken casserole
directions: Stew the chicken.
Remove the bones and skin.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine; mix with stuffing.
Put 1/2 of mixture in casserole dish.
Place chicken over mix.
Pour soup and broth over the chicken.
Spread other 1/2 of stuffing mix over all.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: kelli's chili
directions: Put all ingredients in a slow cooker to cook.
Cook all day.

title: egg gravy
directions: Place eggs in saucepan and cover with water.
Boil for 10 minutes, then peel and cut up.
In another saucepan, place milk, oleo, salt and pepper.
Make a thin paste of flour and water.
Add to milk and oleo.
Add chopped eggs and stir until thickened. Serve over potatoes.
Delicious with fish.

title: cranberry liqueur
directions: Place a full bottle of vodka in an empty washed milk carton. Fill carton with water.
Add a few edible flowers (roses, nasturtiums, chives, etc.).
Freeze.
Peel away carton and wrap ice in an elegant napkin.
Pour vodka over a single olive in a martini glass.
Happy Holidays!!!

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel, slice and cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over carrots.
Chill overnight.
(This can be made 1 or 2 days in advance.)

title: no cook divinity
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine frosting mix, corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water.
Beat on high speed until stiff peaks form, about 5 minutes.

title: candy cookies(makes 4 to 5 dozen)
directions: Melt both bags of chips in a large pan.
Stir in peanut butter.
Let cool completely.
Add nuts and marshmallows; stir so they are covered with chocolate mixture.
Drop the mixture from a spoon onto cookie sheets that are covered with waxed paper.
Put into refrigerator until set and cool.
Then place in containers and store in refrigerator.

title: amish cookies
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and refrigerate for several hours.
Form into small balls and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until light brown.

title: creole pork casserole
directions: Brown pork and onions.
Add tomatoes and put in baking dish. Add cheese and salt.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease baking dish.
Start with layer of thinly sliced potatoes, salt, pepper and butter.	Continue with as many layers as you wish.
Put chopped onion and grated cheese on at least 2 or 3 layers.
Warm milk (microwave is fine).
Pour this over layers of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.	About 15 minutes before done, put cheese on top.

title: ma brush's sauerbraten
directions: In a large pot, put roast and add 1 cup of water and 1 cup of vinegar until meat is completely covered (add evenly).
Add sliced yellow onion and pickling spice.
Cover and soak for 2 days in the refrigerator.
Cook over medium heat until almost done and meat is tender.
Add sugar until sweet and sour tasting (to your own taste).
Add large bottle ketchup.
Finish cooking until meat is done.
Take meat out and thicken gravy.
Add Kitchen Bouquet until gravy is mahogany colored.
Strain gravy.
Slice meat and return to gravy.
Serve over prepared egg noodles.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan the yellow cake mix, 1 egg and stick of butter.

title: barley-mushroom casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 2 teaspoons butter over medium heat.
Add barley and saute, stirring for 1 minute or until lightly browned.
Transfer the barley to small bowl.
Melt remaining 2 teaspoons butter in the casserole dish.
Add onion and saute, stirring for 1 minute.
Add fresh mushrooms and saute, stirring occasionally for 3 minutes.
Return barley to casserole dish.
Add stock, salt, pepper and bay leaf and bring to boil. Transfer to oven and bake, covered, for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until barley is tender.
Before serving, remove and discard bay leaf. Stir in parsley. Serves 6; 169 calories per serving.

title: spinach omelet
directions: Add milk and salt to eggs.
Preheat a nonstick skillet.
Add 1 teaspoon oil or butter and spread with pastry brush.
Add onion. Saute until golden.
Add spinach and mushrooms.
Stir frequently until tender.
Remove from pan.
Add 1 teaspoon oil or butter and spread with brush.
Pour in eggs.
When almost set, spoon vegetables onto one-half.
Cook sightly longer.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Fold uncovered half over.
Slide onto plate.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Heat oven to 475°. In a large bowl mix water and yeast.
Stir in warm water and brown sugar.
Slowly add 5 cups of flour, stirring constantly.
Stir until mixture is smooth and does not stick to the sides of the bowl.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter together; add eggs, soda and buttermilk.
Then add mashed bananas, flour, nuts and flavoring. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna in water until soft; drain.
Brown meat, onion and bell pepper.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
If sauce gets thick, add some water.
In baking dish, place a layer of lasagna noodles, cheeses and then sauce. Repeat 2 or 3 layers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: honey-sesame pork tenderloin
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and sesame oil. Place tenderloins in a heavy plastic bag.
Pour soy mixture over.
Let marinate 2 hours at room temperature or overnight in the refrigerator.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Boil carrots until tender.
Carefully cut in half, lengthwise and depulp the center of each carrot half.
Arrange carrots in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Saute onion and pepper until tender.
Add chopped carrot pulp and pour over carrots.
Melt cheese and pour over carrots.
Bake at 350° until browned and bubbly.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook in slow cooker on high until rice is done.
Stir a few times.
After rice is done, beat eggs and vanilla.

title: microwave raisin bread pudding
directions: Combine milk and butter in a 1-quart glass measure.
Cook at Medium for 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes or until milk is scalded. Quickly stir in eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Meanwhile, arrange bread cubes in a 2-quart microwave-safe dish.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar, raisins and cinnamon.
Pour milk mixture over bread.
Cook, covered with plastic wrap, at Medium for 17 to 19 minutes or until pudding is set.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash tender.
Drain and add salt and pepper to taste and beaten egg.
Fold in all other ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: miz polly's chocolate pie
directions: Stir together sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Separate egg yolks from egg whites. Add 1/2 cup milk to egg yolks.
Mix egg yolks and milk together.
Add remaining milk (1 cup) to sugar mixture and stir. Add milk and egg mixture, then add vanilla. Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour in cooked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except dressing mix.
Put mixture in buttered 9 x 12-inch pan or casserole dish.
Sprinkle the dressing mix over entire top of casserole until covered well (not thick). Then refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator one hour before baking.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 3 prepared layer cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: cat's spiced tea
directions: Blend in blender.
Store in sugar container.

title: instant spice tea or russian tea
directions: Mix well all dry ingredients and store in an airtight jar. To make 1 cup of tea, add 2 to 3 teaspoons mix to 1 cup boiling water and stir well.

title: lasagna
directions: In large heavy pan, lightly brown beef and onion.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, chili and oregano leaves; simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: Place asparagus in baking dish.
Mix in almonds and cheese. Stir in soup.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crackers are brown.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cucumber in sour cream and dill sauce
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice very thin.
Pour boiling water over cucumbers for 1/2 minute.
Drain immediately and cover with ice water.
Drain again and dry.
Mix together the sour cream, vinegar, dill, salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix with cucumbers. Chill.

title: date and nut bread no. 1
directions: Sprinkle the baking soda over the dates, then pour the boiling water over all and let cool.
Cream butter and sugar together with the egg.
Add the sifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix with the dates and water and pour into a loaf tin.
Bake 1 hour in a moderate oven (350°).

title: eagle brand
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Beat until very smooth. May be used immediately or stored in refrigerator until ready to use.
Equals 1 (14-ounce) can Eagle Brand milk.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Pour 1 can sliced apples into a buttered casserole dish (do not use apple pie filling).
Cream in a mixer the butter or margarine and 1 cup sugar.
Add the cheese and flour.
Spread mixture over apples.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ramen slaw(serves 6)
directions: Toss together cabbage, onions, sesame seed, almonds and dry Ramen noodles.
Mix water, oil, sugar, vinegar and Ramen seasoning package to make dressing.
Pour dressing over cabbage mixture and toss.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Can be made a day or two in advance.

title: pineapple surprise salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in warm pineapple juice drained from a can of shredded pineapple.
When mixture has hardened somewhat, add the pineapple and carrots.

title: flank steak pinwheels
directions: Lay flank steak open; sprinkle with pepper.
Top with patchwork of peppers.
Sprinkle evenly with the cheese and then cover with a spinach layer.
Press firmly.
Roll up tightly, beginning along edge and secure the roll with a toothpick at 1 inch intervals.
Slice into 1 inch thick pinwheels, making sure each one is secured with a toothpick.
Lay the slices on a broiler pan and broil about 1 inch from the heat for 6 to 7 minutes, turning after 3 minutes.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Bring to a boil all ingredients except cabbage, bell pepper and onion.
Pour over cabbage, onion and peppers.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours; it will last for about a week.

title: turtle trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to the package directions, stirring in 1 cup of pecans. Bake as directed. Let cool and break into small pieces.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Brown sausage or ham hocks.
Saute chopped vegetables in the drippings and place all the ingredients in a large pot.
Cover ingredients with water.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Thoroughly mix sugar, oil, molasses and 1/4 cup cold water. Add 1 cup flour with soda and spices.
Mix thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour and 1 cup cold water alternately to make a soft dough.
Drop by spoonfuls on a cookie tin (sprayed).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix the chicken, soup, enchilada sauce and diced onion in a large pot.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add Fritos, then pour into a 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish that has been greased.
Bake for 15 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: savory lentil casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake, covered, at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until most of the liquid is absorbed. During the last 20 minutes of baking, top with grated Cheddar or Monterey Jack cheese.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients as listed.
Chill before serving.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Add onion and green pepper to ground beef; continue to cook.
Add tomato sauce to mixture and cook slowly.
Add Tabasco sauce.
Heat chile in another saucepan while meat mixture is cooking.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: You add as much of vegetables as you need for your family.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs, oil, vanilla and cinnamon. Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Add water to peeled sweet potatoes and cook until done. Drain water from sweet potatoes.
Add sugar.
May need to add more until sweetened; mix together.
Add self-rising flour and mix with sugar and sweet potatoes.
Add margarine and sprinkle nutmeg and cinnamon to taste.
If mixture is dry, add small amount homogenized milk.
Does not need to be runny.
Spray 9 x 13 cake pan with Pam.
Bake on 325° to 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until done.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Flour and grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) pans.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl; mix 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pans.
Bake oblong pan 40 to 45 minutes, layers 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost with Sour Cream Frosting.

title: a. j.'s quick baked beans
directions: Dice 1/2 of an onion and put into a glass microwavable bowl. Add juice off of beans.
Cook in microwave for 5 minutes, then add 3 tablespoons brown sugar and beans.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cook for 15 minutes longer and serve.

title: taco lasagna
directions: Cook beef, drain.
Add taco seasoning, garlic, pepper and water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Sprinkle corn meal in 13 x 9-inch pan or even a little larger.
Place 6 shells in bottom overlapping and up sides some.
Layer in order:
1 cup salsa, 1/2 of meat mixture, 1 cup sour cream and 2 cups cheeses.
Repeat stacking with shells.
Place 6 tortillas and remaining salsa on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Remove and add rest of cheese. Bake 10 minutes more.
Let stand before serving.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup barbecue sauce.
Shape into a loaf in a 12 x 8-inch baking pan.
Microwave on High for 12 to 14 minutes or until center is no longer pink.
Drain and turn dish after 6 minutes.
Top with remaining barbecue sauce; let stand 5 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, flour and sugar together.
Add a little milk, egg, oleo and vanilla.
Add rest of milk, a little at a time.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Pour in a 9-inch pie shell. Cool and serve with Cool Whip or make a meringue and brown in a 375° oven.

title: strawberry jello with sour cream
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into mold; congeal.
Add the sour cream on top of the congealed mixture.
Pour remaining Jell-O on top.
Refrigerate.

title: daisy's pancake
directions: Combine flour, milk and salt.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Stir to mix ingredients only.
Mixture will be lumpy.
Pour into small ovenproof skillet in which butter has melted.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and powdered sugar.
Serve with orange marmalade.
Serves 2.

title: hermits
directions: Into a large bowl, measure all ingredients except raisins and nuts.
With mixer at medium speed, beat until well blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Refrigerate, covered, about 3 hours. Preheat oven to 375°.
On greased cookie sheet, drop by heaping tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart. Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown. Remove to wire rack.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Dip green tomato slices in meal batter.
Fry in hot oil until brown.
Turn and brown on other side.
Drain on paper towel to absorb oil.

title: deviled ham dip or spread
directions: Mix three ingredients; chill and serve on crackers or as a dip for vegetables.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut unpeeled zucchini into bite size pieces. Mix carrots and onions with zucchini and cook lightly about 5 minutes and drain.

title: cookie salad
directions: Beat together buttermilk and pudding mix.
Add Cool Whip and drained fruit.
Add cookie pieces before serving.
Save a few to sprinkle on top.
Serve chilled.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans following package directions.
Drain.
In 1 1/2 quart casserole, combine green beans, soup, milk, seasonings, and pimento.
Add 1/2 of the onions.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: In nonstick skillet, saute onions in oil.
Add chicken and cook, turning once, then add rest of ingredients.
Simmer until done, but not dry.
Makes 5 servings.

title: peanut butter no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: cranberry clusters
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the flour, salt and baking powder. Add cranberries, dates and chopped nuts.
Toss until fruit and nuts are evenly coated with flour mixture.
Beat in small bowl until light and fluffy the eggs, sugar and lemon extract.
Pour over fruit and nut mixture.
Mix thoroughly to coat fruit and nuts.
Use small size nonstick muffin tins, dropping a heaping tablespoonful in each.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir in nut meats.
Bake at 350° in greased pans (loaf) for about 50 minutes until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Do not overbake.

title: cappuccino
directions: Heat milk; stir in other ingredients.

title: peanut crisp bars
directions: In a saucepan, combine granulated sugar, corn syrup and salt. Cook and stir until sugar dissolves.
Blend in peanut butter. Stir in cereal.
Pat evenly into a 6 x 10 1/2-inch container or square cake pan.
In small saucepan, melt butter and brown sugar; remove from heat.
Add milk and vanilla.
Stir in powdered sugar; beat smooth.
Spread over cereal mixture.
Chill.
Cut in small bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: neese's sausage cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream sausage with sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with orange juice.
Add applesauce next.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand for 15 minutes in pan before removing from pan.
Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli with linguine
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add onion and peppers.
Saute (over low heat) until done.
Add broth and broccoli, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pour over cooked linguine.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine the two sauces.
Mix well and cook slowly while making the meatballs.
Mix ground beef, corn flakes, onion, salt and pepper.
Form meatballs and drop into sauce.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lime 7-up jello salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello, stir until thoroughly dissolved. Let sit until no longer steaming. Add 7-up. In another bowl cream together cream cheese and drain crushed pineapple. Slowly pour the jello mixture into the creamed mixture. Pour into mold and chill until jello is set.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together with electric mixer.
This is good to serve with bananas, pineapple chunks, white grapes, strawberries and apple slices on a serving tray.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend ingredients.
Great with sliced apples or pears, strawberries and grapes.

title: mole
directions: Note:
May also be used for sauce for enchiladas.

title: strawberry magic
directions: Generously grease bottom only of 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan.
Combine thawed berries and syrup with dry Jell-O and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Blend at low speed; beat 3 minutes at medium.
Pour batter evenly over marshmallows.
Spoon strawberry mixture evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until golden brown and toothpick comes out clean.

title: grandma's white bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast into very warm water in a cup.
Measure; stir in 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Let stand until bubbly and double in volume, about 10 minutes.

title: ann's meatballs
directions: In small mixing bowl dissolve meat loaf mix in hot water.
When water is cool stir in egg.
Add 1/3 can herb sauce, reserve rest for later.
In large bowl combine beef and rice, mix thoroughly and add sauce mixture.
Blend with fork or hands.
Use a roasting pan with rack.
Line with foil and lightly spread Crisco on rack.
Make small meatballs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Place meatballs in ovenproof pan.
Mix sugar in reserved herb sauce then pour over meatballs.
Stir gently to lightly coat each meatball.
Put back in oven for 20 minutes or until sauce is hot.

title: mason city casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole, pack the raw ground beef. Top with minced onion and add the Tater Tots. Add the celery soup and mushroom soup.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or more until meat is done and potatoes are brown on top.

title: "mother-in-law" linguia bread
directions: Let dough sit overnight on greased pan until risen.
Spread one loaf of dough out on a greased cookie sheet right to the edge. Peel casing off of linguia and cut in thin slices.
Lay on top of dough until covered.
Lay slices of roast beef over linguia. Sprinkle with chopped parsley and salt and pepper.
Drizzle small amount of olive oil on top.
(Moisten fingers with water and dampen edges of dough around pan, pulling to edges of pan.)
Spread out remaining loaf of dough and lay out on top.
Pull to edges and pinch together.
Spread crust with melted butter or margarine. Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes.

title: apricot-orange dessert
directions: Drain apricots, reserving
1 cup juice.
Boil juice and dissolve jello in it.
Whip cream cheese and apricots in blender until smooth.
Blend jello, Dream Whip and apricot mix and refrigerate in desired pan.
Can be poured over graham cracker crust before chilling.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichokes.
Add all ingredients.
Heat in microwave for 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chicken log
directions: Bone chicken breasts and wrap each breast in bacon.
Line baking dish with dried beef.
Put chicken in dish.
Mix together and pour over chicken the sour cream, soup and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mama's vegetable soup
directions: Using a large pot, put soup bone (make good broth) and stew meat together with onion, celery and tomatoes.
Add enough water to fill 3/4 pot.
Add salt, pepper and red cayenne pepper.
Cover. Simmer several hours or half or all day.
Skim off fat; discard bone.
Add barley, green pepper, cabbage, carrots, green beans and corn.
Cook for at least 1 hour.
Then add potatoes, turnip and spaghetti.
Correct seasoning, adding more water if necessary. Cook 15 more minutes.
Makes a large amount.

title: homemade corn soup
directions: Boil fryer and debone.
Add all ingredients to broth.
Simmer until veggies tender.
Add lots of black pepper, then chicken. Serve over rice.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Alternate with milk.
Add the raisins and jam.
Mix and add the black walnuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 300° for 45 minutes.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: vacuum cleaner cookies
directions: Combine butter, cake mix and 1 egg.
Pat into well-greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Beat 2 eggs slightly.
Add cream cheese and powdered sugar and mix well.
Add nuts and coconut.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: Cream the sugars, Crisco and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Add vanilla.
Lastly add the rolled oats, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Roll into balls. Bake at 325°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix butter with dressing mix.
Mix 1/2 dressing mixture with squash, soup, sour cream and rest of ingredients. Put mixture into lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining dressing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
A good way to use matured summer squash, just peel, remove seeds and cut up.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: old-fashioned cream pie
directions: Heat the heavy cream in top of double boiler.
Mix the sugar, flour and salt.
Pour hot cream over mixture, stirring well. Return to double boiler and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add egg whites.
Pour into pastry shell and bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes.
Chill and cover with whipped cream topping.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In a large bowl, combine oyster sauce, soy sauce and sesame oil.
Add chicken, tossing to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour. In wok or large nonstick skillet, heat peanut oil.
Add onions and garlic.
Stir-fry 2 minutes until onions are softened.
Stir in chicken mixture.
Stir-fry 2 minutes longer.
Add carrots.
Cook, covered, 3 minutes until carrots are tender-crisp.
Stir in mushrooms, pea pods and corn.
Stir-fry 3 minutes.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Add pineapple and juice to soda.
Mix and set aside.
Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Add pineapple mixture and stir. Add eggs and stir.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Mix the following and pour over cake:

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 2 small loaf pans. Mix sugar and margarine.
Stir in eggs until blended.
Add bananas and water.
Beat 30 seconds.
Stir in dry ingredients, just until moistened.
Stir in nuts.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
I bake it approximately 50 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pans.
Cool completely before slicing. Contains about 120 calories per slice.
"Do not use self-rising flour."

title: helen's punch
directions: Mix water, sugar, orange juice, lemonade, pineapple juice and bananas.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, add Sprite.
Good for showers and weddings.

title: pennsylvania dutch apple torte
directions: Peel and slice apples and place in shallow baking dish.
Sift flour once; measure.
Blend flour with rest of ingredients and spread over top of apples.
Bake in a moderately hot oven at 375° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve with whipped cream or lemon sauce.
Serves 6.

title: parmesan cheese bread
directions: Melt butter in cake pan.
Sprinkle onion and seeds over butter.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Shake biscuits and cheese in a plastic bag, then pour into pan over butter and seeds.
Arrange biscuit pieces so they are only one deep and cook as directed on can.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Remove ice cream from box and put in plastic container in a sink of hot water until very soft.
Crush cookies in a bowl; add Cool Whip.
Then mix in the soft ice cream and stir until blended. Put in freezer until hard.

title: pear relish
directions: *You can also use 2 red and 2 green peppers, if desired.

title: raised sally lunn
directions: Scald milk. Add butter.
Cool to lukewarm. Add well beaten eggs and dissolved yeast. Add to sifted dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down. Transfer to baking pan.
Let rise until double and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread crumbs into an 8 x 1 3/4-inch round ovenware cake dish.
Combine eggs, milk, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in brown sugar and raisins.
Pour mixture into cake dish and place cover on top.
Place dish in larger shallow pan on oven rack.
Pour 1-inch of hot water into larger pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: triple-decker vegetable omelet(makes 4 servings; carb count: 7 grams)
directions: In 8-inch nonstick skillet, over medium-high heat, saut broccoli, bell pepper, carrot, green onions and garlic in 1 teaspoon margarine until tender. Remove from skillet; stir in 1/2 cup cottage cheese. Keep warm. Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning; set aside.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add oil.
Add dry ingredients and zucchini (chopped medium to fine).
Pour into two 5 x 9-inch greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If you use glass pans, bake at 325°.
You may add raisins and nuts to taste.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add sugar, Karo, vanilla and salt to beaten eggs and mix well until smooth.
Add nuts; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream or buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco with sugar; add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flavoring. Sift flour with baking powder 3 times. Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk or sour cream; add to sugar mixture. Alternate adding with buttermilk. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: aunt leta's lemonade
directions: Add all ingredients.
Mix well and pour over ice.
If too tart, add more sugar to taste.

title: applesauce
directions: Wash your hands.
Wash your apple.
Put apple on apple peeler. Put plate under apple peeler.
Turn the handle.
Peeling comes curly off.
Cut the apple in pieces.
Put it in bowl.
Put it in crock-pot and cook it until morning.
Eat it with a spoon.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel and chop or grind pears very fine. Mix pears and sugar in large pot and boil for 30 minutes.
Add crushed pineapple and cook 15 minutes longer.
Put in sterile jars and seal.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Brown chicken in margarine.
Stir in soup, sherry, pepper and onion; cover.
Simmer on low heat for 45 minutes.
Stir often to keep from sticking to pan.
You can add small can of mushrooms for taste (optional).

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat on top of stove (drain).
Boil noodles separately in pot.
Mix Ragu, cottage cheese and hamburger meat together.
Then, in large casserole dish, start layering with noodles, then a layer of meat sauce and then your cheeses.
Cook for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken and zucchini
directions: Start water for rice.
Melt butter in a microwave-safe casserole dish. Stir zucchini through butter. Scoot to edges.
Lay chicken on top. Combine honey, mustard, soy sauce and curry powder.
Brush chicken with 1/2 of this sauce.
Microwave cook for 5 minutes.
Turn chicken; brush with remaining sauce. Cook, covered, for 3 minutes. Check for doneness. Finish cooking, uncovered.
Serve over rice.

title: tennessee creamed chicken
directions: In the melted butter, saute the onion and celery.
Add flour and brown lightly.
Add milk-chicken stock liquid and stir until a medium thick sauce is obtained.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Heat coconut, nuts, brown sugar and butter, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Spread in pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Cool.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Form cakes and dip in bread crumbs.
Fry in vegetable shortening until golden brown. Serves 6.

title: honey balls
directions: Mix well and roll into balls. Roll in crushed wheat cereal or cornflakes. Very nutritious.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Spread chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Grate eggs over chicken.
Heat soup and broth together until smooth.
Pour gently and evenly over eggs.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour evenly and gently over the soup.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.

title: cheater's italian meal
directions: Cook macaroni or any type of noodles according to box directions; drain.
In skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in mushrooms and sauce.
Pour half of the macaroni into a 3-quart casserole.
Add 1 cup cheese; top with half the meat sauce.
Add the remaining macaroni.
Add remaining 1 cup cheese and meat sauce.
Sprinkle top with small amount of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Soak the gelatin in the 1/2 cup of cold water.
Grind or chop the cranberries in grinder or food processor.
Empty into a large mixing bowl.
Add the sugar.
Stir well and let set for about 10 minutes.

title: ritz cracker delight
directions: Crumble crackers until fine, then mix with melted margarine. Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Save 1/3 cup to use on top.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour Bundt pan.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and beat for 5 minutes.
Pour batter in pan.
Bake 1 hour until cake tests done.

title: chicken-fried pork chops
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Combine egg and milk. Dip chops in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs.
In skillet, brown chops on both sides in shortening.
Season with salt. Add water.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dutch oven nachos
directions: This is not a new
recipe.
This
is how we make nachos when we are hunting, fishing, camping, etc.
Cut each tortilla into 6 pieces.
Cook pieces in hot oil until crisp.
Make sure you don't overcook.
Place
on
paper
towels to drain.
Place tortilla pieces on the bottom of your Dutch oven.
Put a slice or pinch of cheese on
each
tortilla piece and put a slice of jalapeno on top.
Put your
lid
on
and
cover
the
lid with briquets
or hot ashes from your campfire.
When the cheese is melted,
remove and serve.
Sometimes a little chopped tomato is nice on top.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in coffee.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Blend into shortening mixture; add mincemeat.

title: company beans
directions: Drain canned beans and corn.
Put beans and corn in 9 x 13-inch oven casserole dish.
Stir in molasses and barbecue sauce. Stir in finely chopped onion and pepper.
Cover with bacon strips. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Remove cover and continue cooking 1/2 hour.

title: peanut cups
directions: Cream together oleo, brown sugar, white sugar and peanut butter.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Make 40 balls and drop into miniature cupcake tins.
(Do not form into a crust like you do for tassies.)
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and immediately press mini peanut butter cup into each cookie.
Wait until cool before taking out of pans.

title: nice salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together good and then add fruit cocktail and oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip last.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onions. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer at 200° for 1 hour.

title: pork and apple bake
directions: Place apples in well-greased baking dish (8-inch square).
Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg; sprinkle over apples.
Coat pork with bread crumbs.
Arrange pork over apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for about 50 minutes.

title: cereal party snack
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt fat in large pan in oven.
Remove pan from oven.
Stir sauces into fat.
Add nuts, pretzels and cereals to mixture and mix well.
Sprinkle with the dry seasonings.
Heat, uncovered, in a 250° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes about 24 small servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry up bacon and chop up.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture into an ovenproof pan (no lid).
Cook for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and cool.
Add vegetables and bottle of dressing.
Mix well and chill several hours or overnight.
This is delicious with hamburgers when you have a cook-out.
I use the colored Twist Trio pasta because it makes my salad much more colorful.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Heat oil in a 4-quart kettle about 3 minutes.
Add corn, cover loosely and shake over the heat until popping stops.
Pour syrup mixture over corn and stir over medium heat until corn is completely coated.
Shape corn into small balls (about 1 1/2-inch).
Makes 16 balls.

title: mushroom burger
directions: Start simmering mushroom soup in small saucepan.
Form 4 to 6 hamburger patties.
Place in frying pan.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce and sprinkle to taste with garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Let bottom brown and flip burgers over.
Now repeat process on this side with Worcestershire sauce, garlic, salt and pepper.

title: ruth's cinnamon rolls
directions: Dip biscuits in butter, then in the brown sugar mixture. Place in buttered muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: beef roast
directions: Place all of the ingredients into a covered baking dish.
Cook at 300° for 3 1/2 hours.
Lid needs to fit loose, so that steam can escape while baking.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Cube bread and cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Spread sausage evenly over bread cubes and cover with egg mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 10.
Serve with fresh or stewed fruit and muffins.
This recipe should be put together and refrigerated at least 6 hours before baking.

title: festive three bread
directions: Stir together thoroughly all-purpose flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine eggs, oil and milk; add to the flour mixture and stir just until blended.
Stir in shredded carrot, coconut, maraschino cherries, raisins and pecans.
Turn into 4 well-greased and floured 16 ounce fruit or vegetable cans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from cans; cool thoroughly on rack.
Wrap in foil; store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 small loaves.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan and heat.
After it starts to boil good, cook for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add vanilla, oats and peanut butter. Spoon out on waxed paper or pour and spread in a pan and cut into squares.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Add parsley, soup, milk and tuna.
Heat and add cheese and let everything melt down.
Cook egg noodles; drain and mix all the ingredients with noodles.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until hot and crispy on top.

title: saturday night special
directions: Saute ground chuck, chopped onion and bell pepper in 1/3 stick butter.
Drain and put in casserole dish.
Add other ingredients and cook in oven at 250° for 2 hours.

title: chicken velvet
directions: Bake in buttered casserole at 300° for one hour.
Bread crumbs and almonds on top if desired.
You can use mushroom soup and if you double the recipe, just use 1 cup mayonnaise.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Thoroughly mix together butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in pecans and frost.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook and chop chicken; save broth.
Dip tortillas in broth. Layer in 9 x 13-inch dish, greased, in this order until you run out:
Tortillas, chicken and onion.
On top of that, layer cheese and sprinkle with chili and garlic powder.
Then pour on soups (mixed together) and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Don't stir.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: deep fried cheese sticks
directions: Dip cheese cubes in flour, then egg mixture, then in flour again. Fry in deep fat fryer until golden brown. Serve with a pizza sauce for dipping.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together and bake in three 9-inch pans or tube pan at 350° until done.

title: pineapple inside cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add shortening, 1/4 cup milk and pineapple juice and beat well.
Add eggs and beat again.
Then add remaining 1/4 cup milk, vanilla and pineapple.
Bake in two 9-inch cake pans in 375° oven about 30 minutes.
Ice with seven-minute icing or your own favorite icing.

title: apple crisp
directions: Wash apples; core and pare thinly.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Mix sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and lemon rind.	Sprinkle over apples and add lemon juice.
Mix flour, sugar and salt with a pastry blender or fork.
Mix butter or margarine with dry ingredients and sprinkle over top apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is slightly browned.

title: fantastic candy snack
directions: Mix the Fruit Loops, marshmallows and pecans together in large bowl.
Melt the white chocolate in double boiler over hot, not boiling, water until melted.
Remove from heat; pour over Fruit Loops, marshmallows and pecans; mix until well coated.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper until chocolate sets.
Store in sealed container.

title: spiced tea
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Leave cinnamon stick in tea for 20 minutes, then remove.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Cook together sugar, vinegar, egg, flour and juice.
Simmer until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool and refrigerate.
Combine apples, 3/4 cup peanuts and pineapple.
Fold in whipped topping, then cooled sauce mixture.
Sprinkle remaining peanuts on top.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Brown onions, celery and green pepper in oil.
Blend in flour, salt, chili powder or Seafood Magic seasoning.
Add tomatoes and vinegar.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cooked and shelled shrimp and cooked peas.
Cook 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, cheese, mayonnaise, onion, chestnuts and celery. Pour into greased or sprayed casserole dish.
Crumble crackers into melted margarine.
Pour over top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: milk chocolate fudge
directions: Butter a 9-inch square pan.
In a heavy 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar, milk, butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Boil and stir for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chips and vanilla.
Add nuts and pour into pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes approximately 5 dozen squares.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
You will need a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased with butter and dusted with flour.

title: apple spice muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg until thick.
Add milk and butter.
Combine mixture.
Fold in apples.
Put in greased tins. Sprinkle with 4 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: four-fruit pies
directions: Pour the fruits into separate saucepans, adding 1/2 cup sugar to each.
Mix the cornstarch and water; divide among the three fruits in the pans and cook until thickened.
Add food color and set off to cool.
Then mix the three fruits together; store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Layer sliced bananas in bottom of baked shells.
Fill with fruit; top with whipped cream.
Makes three 9-inch or four 8-inch pies.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Roll in balls and roll in more Rice Krispies; refrigerate.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook jumbo shells according to package directions.
Drain and cool.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into shells.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon (crisp) and crumble.
Cook beef until no pink remains.
Add onion and saute until tender. Combine beef, onion, catsup, salt, brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and molasses into 3-quart baking dish. Stir gently. Sprinkle with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: In heavy skillet, brown pork chops in small amount of hot shortening.
Pour off fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
For sauce, combine tomato sauce, catsup, onion salt, Worcestershire sauce and liquid smoke; pour over chops.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 1 hour, turning occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and let cool.
Stir oil in cake mix.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add gelatin and beat 5 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour without opening oven door.

title: lemon chess pie 1
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat ingredients just enough to mix well.
Pour into crust.
Reduce heat to 400° and bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes more.

title: grandma's beef barbecue
directions: After you cook beef, cut or pull apart into chunks. Season with garlic, salt and pepper. Simmer in frying pan the onions, green pepper and basil.
Add in beef chunks and 1 bottle or more barbecue sauce. Stir well over low heat for flavor to go through.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook beef.
Add soup, water, Worcestershire and pepper.
Heat through, stirring often.

title: lemonade ice cream
directions: Mix well, freeze and serve.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cream well with electric mixer, then add next 3 ingredients.
Beat until well blended.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, in a lightly greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or two round cake pans.

title: scallop appetizer
directions: Combine wine and water in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil. Add scallops and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain and let cool. Combine scallops and next 5 ingredients in a shallow dish.
Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
To serve, line individual scallop shells with leaf lettuce; top with scallop mixture.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, water, white Karo and salt until it spins a thread from the spoon.
Do not stir while cooking.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 3 tablespoons of cooked mixture.
Cook remaining mixture until it makes a crackling noise in cold water when dropped from a spoon.
Gradually add to egg white mixture; beat until it can be dropped by teaspoonfuls.
Before dropping, add vanilla and chopped pecans.

title: chess squares
directions: Combine cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg and mix well.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix sugar, cream cheese, 2 eggs, vanilla and salt in mixing bowl.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Pour cheese mixture over cake mixture and bake in a 325° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool for several hours before cutting.

title: crispy chicken sandwiches
directions: Combine chicken, soups, pimento, onion and water chestnuts, mixing well.
Spread evenly on 10 slices of bread.
Top with remaining ten slices.
Wrap sandwiches individually in heavy-duty foil and freeze.

title: linguine and spring vegetables
directions: Set a large pot of water on the stove to boil.
Cream the butter with the saffron, 1/8 teaspoon salt and a few pinches of pepper.
Set aside.

title: deer stir-fry
directions: *Adjust to family size the amount of meat.

title: broccoli with stuffing
directions: Combine eggs, onion, soup and mayonnaise.
Place a layer of broccoli in a 2-quart casserole.
Add a layer of cheese and pour a small amount of sauce over top.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Top with stuffing mix and sprinkle butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over hamburger buns with potato chips and pickle.

title: baked donuts
directions: Mix all together.
Fill paper cupcake liners 1/2 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While still warm, peel off paper liners and shake in cinnamon and sugar.

title: fettuccine with vegetables
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large pot.
Add fettuccine and carrots; cook over medium heat for 6 minutes.
Add broccoli; continue cooking until carrots and broccoli are crisply tender, 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Rinse with hot water; set aside.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine in a boiler the water, sugar, jello and cornstarch and cook until thick.
Pour into cooled pie shell and let cool.
Then add sliced strawberries, pressing into jello mix and top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: three-in-one hamburger mix
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add beef and brown.
Drain off excess fat.
Add rest of ingredients; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Makes 4 cups.
Use on buns as Sloppy Joes or in following recipe:

title: pineapple sherbet
directions: Dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1 quart uv boilin' watah 'n sugah...let this cum to a boil 'n cool...then pore in the lemun juice 'n crushed pineapple 'n let freeze...when frozen add kream 'n milk 'n start crankin' til frozen stiff...hit'll make about 6 quarts.

title: skillet stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet; drain.
Stir in broth, mushrooms, noodles, water, catsup and garlic powder. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until noodles become tender.
(A small amount of water can be added if necessary.)
Stir in sour cream.
Heat just until hot and serve.
Serves 5.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, water and oleo to a slow boil.
Let it boil for 1 1/2 minutes, then take it off stove.
Add the peanut butter and oats.
Drop off spoon onto waxed paper or tinfoil on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until cool.

title: ham sandwiches
directions: Combine and chop finely the ham, cheese, onions and eggs.
Add mayonnaise and chili sauce; mix well.
Spoon onto buns.
Wrap buns in foil and bake 10 minutes at 375°.
These freeze well and can be kept a month in freezer.

title: dirt
directions: Beat cheese and sugar together. In a separate bowl, mix pudding, milk, vanilla and Cool Whip. Use large bowl and fold cheese and

sugar mixture into pudding, milk, vanilla and Cool Whip. Crush Oreos in a blender until crumbly. Do 3 to 4 cookies at a time. Put layer of crumbs in bottom of cake pan, then layer of mix. Repeat until top layer is crumbs. Chill before serving.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Put milk in saucepan and add margarine.
Cook until it boils. Meanwhile, mix cornstarch, sugar, egg yolks and 1/4 cup milk.
When milk and margarine starts to boil, add cornstarch mixture.
Stir until thickened.
Add 1 cup coconut and vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie crust.
Add a pinch of cream of tartar to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Add 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Beat until whites stand in peaks.
Add 1 teaspoon cornstarch.
Pour onto pie and sprinkle with coconut.
Cook until browned at 350°.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift the sugar so it is fine grain; reserve 1/2 cup of this to be added to flour.
Beat the egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and salt.
Continue beating until egg whites are glossy, fine grained and will stand up in a stiff point.
Add gradually, gently beating and folding after each addition, 1 cup sugar, flavoring and 1 cup sifted cake flour which has been sifted 3 times with 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour batter into pan.	Gently cut through batter with knife to break air bubbles.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in liquid Butter Buds; coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot spiced wine
directions: Combine ingredients in a large saucepan and heat well. Transfer to a warmed crockpot to keep warm.
Add sliced orange and lemon.

title: slime
directions: Slime, a product of Mattel Toy Corporation, is a reversible crosslinking gel, made from guar gum and Borax.
Powdered guar gum is available from health food stores.

title: swiss and bacon squares
directions: Mix Bisquick and water; mix until it forms a ball.
Beat 20 times.
Place on floured board and knead 10 times.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place dough in bottom of dish and press over bottom and 1/2-inch up sides.
Spread cheese over dough.
Put crumbled bacon over cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and salt together (mix well).
Pour over bacon.
Bake at 425° for approximately 20 minutes or until edges are golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: In bowl, mix flour, brown sugar, oatmeal and butter.
Press 3/4 of mixture into bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Then cover with rhubarb.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl on medium speed, beat together eggs, pumpkin, sugar, brown sugar and oil.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Beat into pumpkin mixture 1 cup at a time on low speed.
Scrape sides of bowl until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center of loaf comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely on a wire rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Tear angel food cake into little pieces and put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press down.
Mix pudding as directed on package. Pour over cake.
Drain pineapple dry; put over pudding.
Add the strawberries, thawed and drained.
Spread Cool Whip over the strawberries.
Refrigerate!

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix crabmeat, cream cheese and a little cream in a bowl. Next, mix in Worcestershire sauce, onion and mayonnaise.
It will be thick.
Spread in a 9-inch pie plate.
Grate 2 slices of cheese over top and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Serve hot with firm crackers.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles 10 minutes.
Drain and add cheese according to package directions.
Layer 9 x 12-inch pan as follows: *1/2 macaroni and cheese mixture, 1/2 tomato sauce, sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese, top with pepperoni, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Repeat 1 time*.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Heat buttermilk to lukewarm.
Add yeast to buttermilk.
Make a well in the flour mixture and add buttermilk. Stir until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn out to floured board and knead until smooth.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut out with biscuit cutter.
Place one biscuit on top of the other, spreading melted butter between and on top of each.
Let rise or may freeze them.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: traditional potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onion with grating disc of food processor or large holes of a hand grater.
Squeeze mixture to get out as much liquid as possible.
Transfer to bowl; add egg, salt, pepper, flour and baking powder.
Mix together until well blended by hand. Heat 1/2 cup oil in deep skillet.

title: sukiyaki
directions: In wok or skillet, brown suet and add chopped vegetables. Cook until vegetables are semi-tender.
Remove suet and add all liquid and sugar.
Bring to a hard boil and add meat.
Continue cooking until meat is done.
Serve.
Makes 6 good size servings.

title: caramel sweet potatoes
directions: Mash the potatoes.
Add the other ingredients, except pecans. Blend well.
Place in greased dish.
Make "well" in center and sprinkle pecans on top.
Heat at 350°. Just before serving, put the Caramel Sauce on.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix well to form batter.
Add crab meat or fish.
Pat into cakes and saute in butter or margarine until browned.
(May also be deep fried.)

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until hot.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° until thick.

title: pea salad
directions: Cut lettuce in small pieces. Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl. Salt and pepper to taste. In another small bowl, mix mayonnaise and sugar together. Mix this into bigger bowl. If not moist enough, add more mayonnaise. Refrigerate 2 hours and serve.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla and cook. After mixture starts to thicken, add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Makes 2 deep dish pies or 3 regular pies.

title: spinach orange toss
directions: Place spinach in a large salad bowl.
Add oranges and mushrooms.
Toss lightly to mix.

title: barley, beef and kale soup(serves 8)
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven or large heavy saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and meat; cook until well browned. Add broth, barley, thyme and salt. Bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 1 hour or until barley and meat are almost tender. Add mushrooms and kale or other greens. Cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes more until kale is cooked and meat and barley are tender.

title: microwave oven-fried chicken
directions: Mix biscuit mix, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken.
Put in pan skin side up.
Cover with wax paper and cook on High for 10 minutes.
Rotate dish and cook until done, 8 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate bites
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in double boiler. Add sugar and mix. Beat in eggs 1 at a time. Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Pour in greased and floured 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool in pan. Put pan in fridge and chill. Take out and cut into bite-size pieces. Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: creole franks
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in 1 tablespoon butter until tender.
Add soup, tomatoes, pepper, sugar and chili powder.
Stir well.
Simmer about 40 minutes and serve on rice.

title: aunt viv's zucchini soup
directions: Cook zucchini in water with bouillon.
Add carrot, potato and turnip.
In small frypan, saute an onion in margarine and add to mixture.
Cool.
Then puree all ingredients in blender.
Add 3/4 teaspoon dill to the puree and salt and pepper to taste.
Season with 1/2 to 3/4 tablespoon wine vinegar.
Serve hot or cold.
(If soup becomes thick, it can be thinned out with more bouillon.)

title: easy shepherd's pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Add garlic salt, pepper and salt to browned and drained ground chuck.
Heat, then add tomato sauce.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Fill bottoms of pie crusts with mashed potatoes, then spread meat mixture over mashed potatoes.
Top with shredded cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Cut in pie wedges.
Mmm - a meal in one.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet or wok over high heat. Add the chicken and stir-fry for 4 to 5 minutes or until no pink remains. Add the pineapple chunks, water chestnuts, broccoli and bell pepper. Stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes or until the vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: Wash and drain cranberries, chop in food processor.
Chop seeded, unpeeled oranges.
Drain pineapple and mash out juice. Use juice from pineapple for another use or discard.
Add sugar to cranberries, oranges and pineapple and mix well.
Add jello to water and mix into cranberry mixture.
Pour into bowl and chill until set.
Delicious with Thanksgiving turkey.

title: strawberry fritters
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Gradually stir in milk, then beaten eggs.
Fold in berries.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat (375°) in skillet and fry 3 to 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and roll in confectioners sugar. Serve with Strawberry Sauce.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid. Refrigerate 1 hour or until slightly thickened.
Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon into 6 cup mold.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
To loosen mold, dip into hot water for about 15 seconds.

title: pina colada
directions: Shake with 1/2 cup crushed ice and use blender.
