Pour into tall glass filled with ice cubes.
Add cherry.
Superb coconut accent!

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and chilies in large pan.
Drain well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with Fritos, grated cheese and sour cream. Place crushed Fritos in bowl, ladle in soup and top with grated cheese and sour cream.

title: fruit filling cake
directions: *Use apples, apricots, peaches, pineapple or berries for filling.

title: green beans tuscany
directions: Cook beans in boiling water until just tender.
Drain and cover with cloth.
Saute beans in butter, oil and herbs for 1 minute.
Stir over low heat for 5 minutes.
Mix in Parmesan cheese and serve at once.

title: fruit dip
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of milk if necessary.
Serve with any kind of fresh fruit.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Grease bottom of large pan.
Place frozen rolls in pan (about 1/2 inch apart).
Fry and drain sausage.
Spread sausage and cheese on top of rolls.
Cover with towel and let rolls rise overnight.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk completely.
Blend in spices and pumpkin and chill to serve.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain pineapple and apricots, saving liquid. Cut up apricots. Dissolve apricot jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add fruit juice to make 3 1/2 cups.
Add fruit.
Put into a square pan (9 x 9-inch).
Cool until set.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: In a small bowl, combine soup, chicken, 1/2 cup cheese and peppers.
Top half of each tortilla with about 1/4 cup of mixture, spreading evenly over tortilla.
Moisten edges of tortillas with water and fold over, pressing to seal the edges.

title: baked pork tenderloin
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Melt shortening.
Flour meat and add to hot shortening.
Brown well.
Remove, drain and place in baking dish.
Cover with thin gravy and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and bake 1 hour at 350° or bake 1 hour and 40 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat margarine over low heat, add onion; saute.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat, stir in broth and milk. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute. Stir in chicken and vegetables.

title: steamed veggies
directions: Cut in chunks or thick slices.
Use a wire steamer in saucepan or electric steamer.
One kind of vegetable or a mixture may be used.
Layer potatoes, carrots and onions.
Steam about 10 minutes. Add another layer of quick cooking vegetables, squash, broccoli or cauliflower.
Steam another 10 minutes.
Butter and season as desired.

title: easy french dressing
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, catsup, onion, oil, salt and pepper until well mixed. Store in refrigerator.
Shake well.

title: children's choice chinese pepper steak
directions: Partially thaw meat, slice into thin strips.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and ginger and stir into soy sauce.
Pour mixture over meat and stir.
Cut green peppers into 1-inch squares, tomatoes into wedges.
Brown meat, 1/3 at a time, in hot oil and remove from pan.
Reduce heat, add green peppers, cook until crisp-tender, 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir in meat and tomatoes and heat through.
Makes 4 servings with 283 calories.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles until done.
Mix sour cream, eggs, salt and pepper.
Mix both bags of cheese and cook for 35 minutes.

title: margarita
directions: Rub rim of glass with lime peel.
Dip rim in salt; set aside. Over ice in cocktail shaker or large glass, pour remaining ingredients.
Stir; carefully pour into the prepared cocktail glass.

title: consomme rice
directions: Let come to a boil and then bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: eggnog log
directions: In bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add nutmeg, egg and extracts.
Mix well.
Stir in flour.
Chill dough for easier handling.
On a lightly floured surface, shape dough into 1/2-inch diameter rolls.
Cut into 3-inch long pieces.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on rack and frost.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water in bowl.
Combine gelatin mixture with pineapple juice, lemonade concentrate, almond extract and cold water in large freezer container.
Freeze for 3 to 4 days.
Let thaw for 6 hours before serving; stir.
Pour into punch bowl; ladle into punch cups. Yield: 20 servings.

title: mint brownies
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan; cool.

title: low calorie chili(280 calories per serving)
directions: In large pot over medium heat in hot oil, cook celery, onions, green pepper and garlic until onions are tender, about 5 minutes. Add meat and cook until meat is browned, stirring occasionally. Stir in kidney beans, tomatoes and their liquid, salt and 1 1/2 teaspoons chili powder; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 40 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Just before serving, stir in enough chili powder to give desired "hotness". Makes 6 servings.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Mix all dry ingredients with shortening. Cut in shortening.
Add all moist ingredients, knead on hard, floured surface.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes until golden.

title: buttery pasta with shrimp
directions: Use
your
favorite meat loaf mixture and your favorite bread stuffing
(homemade
or Stove Top).
On a piece of waxed paper, pat
out
meat
loaf mixture in a rectangle to 1/4-inch thick. Spread
stuffing
over
top; roll as you would a jelly roll. Carefully
place on a baking sheet; bake as you would a regular meat loaf.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in large punch bowl.

title: india relish
directions: Chop coarsely the tomatoes, apples, onions and pepper. Combine all ingredients and cook slowly, stirring occasionally, about 1 1/2 hours or until mixture is thick and clear.
Ladle into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal at once.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Set oven to 350°. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. In a large mixing bowl, add ingredients one at a time. Mix or beat well after each addition. Pour into pans and bake for 45 to 60 minutes or until a pick inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool 5 minutes before removing from pan. Makes 2 loaves.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel the potatoes and boil until tender. Mash with butter, sour cream, onion flakes, parsley, salt and pepper.
Place into greased baking dish. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbages
directions: Fry onion in a little butter until soft.
Add meat and brown. Add cooked rice; let cool.
Boil water in a large pan.
Steam cabbage in water and cut off leaves, 1 at a time.
Drain on towel. Cut off thick part at the bottom of leaf.
Put 1 to 2 tablespoons of filling in bottom of leaf, fold over both sides and roll.
Line bottom of baking dish with scraps of cabbage.
Use cut up core and small leaves for cover.
Add can of tomato sauce or tomatoes, even soup.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: elizabeth pond's coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together; beat egg, add sugar and flour a little at a time to egg, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla; melt butter, add to mixture after the coconut.
Beat with an electric mixer until mixed well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake until done.

title: baked lemon pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and pale.
Gradually add skim milk, lemon rind, lemon juice and oleo.
Beat well.
Combine 1/3 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the egg yolk mixture and beat well.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add remaining sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time until soft peaks form.
Gently stir 1/4 of mixture into egg yolk mixture.
Fold in rest of whites.
Put in 1-quart casserole.
Set in pan of hot water.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes until top is set.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cool.
Drain all vegetables in a colander.
Mix vegetables in marinade, refrigerate.
Prepare at least 12 hours before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Roll into small balls and bake on a lightly greased cookie sheet in a 350° to 375° oven until lightly browned.

title: meat 'n potato skillet supper
directions: In skillet, lightly brown luncheon meat (which has been cut into strips) and onion in shortening.
Blend in soup and milk.
Add cubed potatoes, chopped parsley and pepper.
Cook over low heat about 10 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: double fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft ball (236°).
Remove from heat; add chocolate pieces, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts. Beat until chips are melted and blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: turkey burgers
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Form patties; cook in a non-stick skillet, browning both sides until done.
Serve on buns with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Fry or bake chicken; shred chicken.
Sprinkle lemon pepper spice on chicken pieces.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add 2 cups cream of chicken soup, 3 to 4 tablespoons butter, 3 to 4 tablespoons lemon juice, sprinkle Mrs. Dash seasoning over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until done.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.
Makes enough for whole family.

title: coconut balls
directions: Cook first 6
ingredients
5 minutes after it starts to bubble.
Add Rice
Krispies
and pecans.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper and
roll
into small balls.
Then roll in coconut flakes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes on top rack of 325° oven.

title: microwave broccoli
directions: Place
frozen
broccoli
in 2 quart greased glass casserole. Microwave
on High for 5 or 6 minutes, covered, stirring once. Drain.
Sprinkle cheese over broccoli.
Dilute soup with evaporated milk.
Pour over broccoli and cheese.
Microwave for 6 minutes on Reheat setting.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle onion rings
over
top of casserole.
Return casserole, uncovered, to oven.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: norwegian potato soup
directions: Add all vegetables to meat stock.
Season to taste and simmer for one hour.
Combine beef, egg, milk and seasonings.
Form into very small meatballs.
Drop meatballs into boiling soup and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: blondies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes before cutting and removing from pan.

title: ray hutchison's homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: These ingredients are for a 1-gallon freezer; multiply or reduce proportionately for 1/2 to 1 1/2-gallon freezers.
Blend eggs, sugar, half and half and whipping cream in mixer until sugar dissolves.
Dissolve Junket in small amount of milk.
Blend all ingredients, adding Eagle Brand milk and vanilla until mixture is smooth.
Pour into freezer can.
Fill to capacity with whole milk and freeze according to freezer directions.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix in horseradish; spread on ham and roll up.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.
Slice in bite size pieces.
Serve.

title: cream cheese pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt in a bowl. Cut in chilled butter, will look like peas. Then mix in cream cheese. Chill 1 hour. Roll and cut to size of pie pan.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, brown sugar, white sugar, egg.
Now sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon two times.
Mix into the creamed mixture, alternating with applesauce. Nutmeats and dates may be added.
Shape in a roll and chill.
Cut in 1/4 inch slices and bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: gail bellingrath's crybabies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs and molasses.
Beat in other ingredients.
Roll 1-inch diameter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: blueberry-lemon bread
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Cut in shortening, using pastry cutter until texture of coarse crumbs.
Combine egg, milk and vanilla; add to flour mixture at once.
Stir very little.
Put in greased and floured muffin tins or drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 14 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix 1st five ingredients and let marinate for 2 hours.
Before serving mix in enough mayonnaise to coat other ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
(Greek seasoning is good, also.)
Serves 4.

title: old fashioned corn bread
directions: Combine buttermilk, soda, salt and egg.
Add enough cornmeal to make a thin batter.
Grease an iron skillet good and have it hot before pouring in the batter.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: ham hawaiian salad
directions: Mix fruits, vegetables and meat together.
Add soy sauce to Hawaiian dressing; toss just before serving.
Serves 36.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Stir together flours, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat egg and milk to blend; add flour mixture with oil.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake in a 375° oven until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean, for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water from the top.
Add sugar and oil to dissolved yeast mixture.
Combine the dry ingredients; best to sift together.
Add buttermilk and liquid mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water until they are barely fork-tender.
Drain.
Add green pepper and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Pour over vegetables. Let set overnight.
Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: shells and grapes
directions: Cook macaroni "al dente" (slightly underdone).
Drain.
While hot, combine with grapes, scallions, cheese, salt, pepper and garlic.
Combine mayonnaise and lemon juice; stir well.
Stir into macaroni until evenly mixed.
Refrigerate, covered, for several hours or overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: shaker daily bread
directions: Mix the warm water and yeast; let stand 5 minutes.
Add the warm milk, melted butter, salt, sugar and 3 cups flour to yeast mixture.
Mix together for about 10 minutes.
Add 2 more cups flour.
Knead until elastic.
Let rise; punch down.
Let rise again; punch down.
Cut into 2 pieces.
Shape into loaves.
Put in two oiled loaf pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: picnic macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain and cool.
Mix macaroni and the remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly; chill.
Serves 6.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from grease and drain.
Saute onion in bacon grease.
Stir in vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper. Add bacon back into grease and vinegar mixture.
Bring to a boil and then pour over potatoes.
Keep over low heat to serve warm.

title: double fruit shake
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on high speed until smooth.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef, do not drain. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and sugar; set aside.
Beat eggs; blend in milk and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
In a large frying pan or iron skillet, pour enough oil to cover the bottom by 1/2 inch. Heat to just short of smoking, 365°.
Carefully pour batter into a small funnel while holding finger to bottom.
Drop batter in oil by releasing finger.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chili con queso
directions: In pan, saute margarine, onion and tomatoes.
Lower heat.
Add cheese, milk and peppers with juice.
Stir until cheese is melted. Serve with Doritos.

title: chicken souffle(club member: mindy daniels)
directions: Trim and cube bread. Place in greased 9-inch pan. Mix cheese, chicken, eggs, soup and 1/2 cup mayonnaise. Pour over chicken-cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: lazy daisy salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread in a dish and top with remaining whipped topping.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Chill.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine in order given and pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer or until firm.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift and measure flour; resift flour with soda.
Cream soft butter; add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in sour cream.
Add dry ingredients, 1/2 cup at a time, beating constantly.
Stir in flavoring.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Place pan on rack to cool 5 minutes. Serve plain.
This cake freezes well.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Mix soup and tomatoes.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Cover and bake for 1 hour if chicken pieces with bone.
Less time if deboned chicken breasts.
Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Blend all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat for 3 minutes at high speed.
Scrape bowl often.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until it springs back when touched lightly in center.
Cool right side up for 25 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Serve with your favorite topping.

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 12-inch pan, put pie filling and pineapple in bottom of pan; slightly mix.
Pour dry cake mix over fruit.
Drizzle margarine across top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: In saucepan, mix milk and chocolate.
Stir until chocolate is melted; remove from heat.
In separate bowl, whisk egg, sugar, cornstarch and vanilla.
Slowly whisk in part of the chocolate mixture, then whisk back into pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick, then pour into pie crust or pudding dishes.
Let cool.

title: pan-fried tomato rounds
directions: Season tomato slices with salt and pepper.
Place on a large plate.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix.
Beat well and pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
(May add slivered almonds or chopped pecans before baking.)

title: seasoned salt
directions: Place all in blender container.
Blend on high speed until finely chopped, about 30 seconds.
Store in salt shakers or tightly covered jar.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix over it.
Pour melted margarine over that and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: cranberry glaze for ham
directions: Combine sugar, nutmeg and cornstarch in a small saucepan.
Add cranberry juice and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Add cranberries and bring to a boil once more.

title: best ever chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: poor man's steak and gravy
directions: Combine beef, cracker crumbs, water, salt and pepper; mix well and spread in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and
place in oblong Pyrex dish.
Bake one hour at 350°. Can be frozen before baking.

title: oven-steamed rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2-quart ungreased casserole with tight fitting lid, mix rice, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter. Pour boiling water over rice; stir with fork to melt butter.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes (do not lift the lid).
To serve, fluff up rice lightly with a fork to mix well.

title: goulash(use leftovers)
directions: Place about 3/4 inch mashed potatoes in bottom of casserole. Saute hamburger, onions and garlic together and put over mashed potatoes.
Pour peas and corn over meat and potatoes, then put more mashed potatoes over that.
Bake 30 minutes in 325° oven. Dab butter over top.

title: common sugar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in 2 (9-inch) greased pans. Sprinkle top of batter with 10x sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Test center with toothpick.

title: lasagna quiche
directions: Roll 1 package of crescent rolls to fit the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 1/4 pound of each:
ham, salami and cheese and 1 jar of peppers.
Combine 5 eggs with Parmesan cheese and pour half over layer.
Layer 1/4 pound of each: ham, salami and cheese and 1 jar of peppers.
Top with rest of egg mixture.

title: caramel pecan brownies
directions: In small saucepan, cook and stir caramels and milk over low heat until caramels are melted.
Set aside.
Beat eggs; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in butter, caramel mixture and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients; stir into caramel mixture.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and put in strainer.
Cut up all vegetables real fine.
Mix all together.
Refrigerate to a chill before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together; chill.
Shape in a ball.
Can be rolled in nuts.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Plantain
may
be
located in the vegetable area of the market.
It resembles a banana in appearance.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate, peanut butter and butter in microwave until smooth.
Pour over Crispix cereal in large bowl.
Stir until coated.
Be careful not to crush cereal.
Put mixture in large plastic bag with powdered sugar.
Mix or shake until cereal is well coated with sugar.

title: scalloped chicken delight
directions: In skillet, saute celery, onion, green pepper and margarine. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken broth and mushroom pieces in their liquid.
Stir until thickened.
In large bowl, beat eggs until light.
Blend in sour cream.
Very gradually and stirring constantly, add hot broth mixture to eggs.
When blended, toss in chicken and cubed stuffing.
Place in greased 12 x 18-inch casserole.
Top with Parmesan cheese and dash of paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crabmeat hors d'oeuvres
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Add minced or grated onion.
Mix well.
Spread on plate or platter about 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle crabmeat on top.
Mix chili sauce, horseradish and lemon juice.
(For hotter sauce, add more horseradish.) Spread sauce over crabmeat.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat caramels and 1/4 cup of the milk, stirring constantly, until caramels are melted.
Keep warm.
Mix dry cake mix, margarine, remaining milk and pecans.
Spread 1/2 of the dough (1 1/2 cups) in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes; remove from oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips.
Drizzle caramel mixture over chocolate chips.
Drop remaining dough onto caramel layers, spreading evenly.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: fudgy chocolate layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 inch round cake pans.
In a saucepan, melt butter and chocolate, stirring, over low heat.
Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in large bowl of electric mixer.
Add chocolate mixture, buttermilk and eggs.
Beat on low speed for 1 minute; increase speed to high and beat until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes.
Divide batter between cake pans.
Bake until cakes spring back when gently pressed, 25 to 30 minutes; cool in pans 5 minutes; invert onto wire rack.
Meanwhile, bring cream just to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips; mix until frosting is smooth and starts to thicken.
Place 1 cooled layer on cake plate.
Spread with 1/3 cup frosting.
Top with second layer.
Frost top and side of cake with remaining frosting.

title: sweet pea salad
directions: Chill peas in can.
Drain water and all ingredients.
Add mayonnaise to taste.
Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with egg.

title: pie crust(cheese cake)
directions: Mix with hands.
Press into pie pan.
Bake at 350°
for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool before adding cheese cake.

title: nut and poppy seed rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast into 1 tablespoon flour, 1 tablespoon sugar and 2 tablespoons water.
Sift flour and add salt and sugar.
Beat egg yolks and add to milk and yeast mixture that is doubled and bubbly.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: In top of double boiler over hot water, mix lightly beaten egg yolks, sugar, lemon juice and cold water. Cook and heat over simmering water for 10 to 15 minutes, or until mixture thickens. Remove from heat and add rind. Set aside.

title: banana pudding
directions: Pour milk into deep bowl add pudding mix, blend until thick. Add sour cream and half of cool whip.
Blend until thick.
Make your pudding in layers.
Vanilla wafers first followed by bananas, then pudding.
Top with remaining cool whip.
Chill before serving.
Makes a 9 x 13 serving container.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Unroll the crescent rolls and press together at the seams on a large cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Mix the cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth and spread evenly over crust.
Mix vegetables and spread over the cream cheese mixture and sprinkle cheese over the vegetables.
Press with hand, cut into squares and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: cheese spread
directions: Blend together.
Add garlic powder, paprika, chili powder and red pepper to taste.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Heat oil in a large pan for 1 minute.
Add finely chopped onion and red pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add garlic, beans, rice, broth, pepper flakes, crumbled thyme and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until rice is tender and liquid is gone, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of cheese over each serving.
Eat with pumpernickel bread and butter.

title: yummy fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly except fruit.
I triple this for a party.
Cut fruit in pieces suitable for dipping.
Enjoy! Guests will love this.

title: crab-shrimp casserole
directions: Saute 1/4 cup butter with 1/4 cup minced onion. Add the flour, salt, pepper, Accent and mustard; blend well.
Add milk; thicken. Add shrimp, crab meat and sherry, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add the sour cream, parsley and Cheddar cheese.
Layer sauce alternately with bread crumbs in casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese strata
directions: Butter lightly 12 slices of bread.
Arrange 6 slices in the bottom of 9x13 baking dish.
Cover with 6 slices of cheese or 2 cups grated cheese.
Top with remaining bread.
Beat together the milk, eggs, mustard and salt and pour over the bread.
Bake 45 minutes or until puffed and golden. May be prepared in advance and refrigerated before baking.
Bake in 350° preheated oven.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. In a large bowl, mix all dry ingredients together.
In another bowl, beat eggs and add them to the dry mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well. Divide batter evenly and pour into prepared pans.
Bake in preheated oven for 60 to 70 minutes. Test with toothpick.
Let bread cool in pans 10 minutes on wire racks.
Remove from pans.
Let cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chocolate mocha sugar
directions: Place sugar in a small bowl.
Add cocoa, almond extract and cinnamon and mix well.
Store in an airtight container.
Use to sweeten coffee to taste.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: jumbo fudge cookies
directions: Heat oven to 370°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Mix brownie mix, flour, oil, water and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in nuts or candy.
Drop by scant 1/4 cupful 3-inches apart onto cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hunt camp chili
directions: Brown ground beef in hot skillet.
Saute cut-up cooking onions and add to ground beef.
Drain and rinse kidney beans and add to beef mixture.
Add tomatoes, juice, chili peppers and salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat for several hours.
(Add more chili peppers, if desired.)

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: Cook
chicken
in the butter for 10
minutes
or
until brown on both sides.
Stir in soup, water
and
pepper.
Boil, add the broccoli and reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until chicken and broccoli is done.

title: singapore chicken and black bean salad
directions: In a blender place picante sauce, vinegar, peanut butter and garlic.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Toss salad greens, cilantro, beans and onions with 1/2 cup picante sauce mixture until evenly coated.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix and cook on low heat the salad dressing, milk and flour until thickened.
Slice zucchini, onion and tomatoes, arranging in casserole.
Pour cooked mixture over all; top with crumbled cracker crumbs and Mozzarella cheese.
Dot with margarine; salt and pepper, or Mrs. Dash.
Bake at 350° until zucchini is tender.

title: gourmet golden squash
directions: Prepare and boil cubed squash.
Mash fine.
Stir in all ingredients.
Turn mixture into ungreased 1-quart casserole. Cook, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: west virginia black walnut cake
directions: Run nuts, raisins and coconut through food chopper. Cream shortening and sugar together until fluffy. Add eggs. Add milk in which soda has been dissolved alternately with allspice and flour. Add jam. Add nuts, raisins and coconut by stirring in. Mix thoroughly and bake 1 hour in a tube pan at 350°.

title: tree salad
directions: Toss all the ingredients.

title: chili bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off liquid; saute onion.
Mix with all ingredients except Jiffy corn muffin mix.
Put mixture in large 11 x 14-inch dish and microwave until very hot (should be bubbly around the edge).
Heat conventional oven to 350°.
Mix Jiffy corn muffin mix according to directions on box (add extra liquid). Remove dish from microwave.
Pour muffin mix over top.
Put in conventional oven and bake until top is cooked; top will begin to turn brown.
Do not overcook.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix by
hand.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream and add oregano, parsley, garlic and other vegetables.
Put into casserole dish. Top with pizza sauce.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until bubbling at 350°.
Serve with crackers or bread sticks.

title: sour cream fruit dip
directions: Stir together sour cream, preserves (cut up large pieces of fruit) and cinnamon.
Chill up to 24 hours.
Serve dip with fruit. Makes 1 cup (8 servings).

title: sawdust pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir by hand.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake in oven about 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Melt cream cheese and butter.
Slice artichoke hearts and place in lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Combine spinach, cream cheese mix and lemon juice.
Spoon over artichokes.
Sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ladyfinger cheese cake
directions: Beat heavy cream and refrigerate. Blend together softened cream cheese, sugar, milk and vanilla. Fold in whipped cream. Line bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan with ladyfinger halves (leave in strips, don't separate).
Pour in half of the mixture.
Layer with remaining ladyfingers.
Pour in rest of mixture.
Top with fruit pie filling.
Refrigerate at least overnight, if not longer.

title: fireman's special
directions: Slide out contents of corned beef hash.
Cut into 5 slices. Fry in hot fat in heavy skillet over hot coals.
Serve on toasted buns with mustard or chili sauce.
Accompany with fresh onions and steaming mugs of coffee.

title: sole stuffed with crabmeat dressing
directions: Place breadcrumbs in large bowl and add just enough milk to make a loose dressing.
Set aside.
Melt butter in large skillet and saute mushrooms.
Add them to breadcrumbs in bowl.
Stir in parsley, eggs, salt, pepper and nutmeg and blend well.
Fold in shrimp and crabmeat.
Wash fillets and salt and pepper well on both sides.
Place 3 fillets skin side down in a greased glass baking dish.
Spoon breadcrumb stuffing over fillets.
Cover with remaining 3 fillets, skin side up.
Fasten stuffed fillets together, using 3 toothpicks per fillet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Baste frequently while baking with melted butter.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter. Press into bottom and halfway up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan. In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar.
Add sour cream, beating until fluffy.
Add lemon rind and vanilla; add eggs, one at a time, beating until blended and pour into pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 60 minutes. turn off oven and leave door ajar for 60 minutes.
Remove from oven, cool and refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.
If desired, garnish with fruit.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 sticks of butter (not melted), eggs and confectioners sugar together.
Mix for 15 minutes.
Pour on top of graham crackers.
Then slice bananas on top of mixture. Layer bananas.
On top of bananas, put crushed pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.
Great for a hot summer day.

title: lemon parsley butter
directions: Mix.
Use with poultry, veal, seafood, broccoli, spinach and rice.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Wash jars. In bottom of each jar place the dill, hot pepper, garlic, mustard seed, celery seed and pickling spice. Pack cold cucumbers on top of this. Make a solution of the vinegar, water, sugar and canning salt. Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers. Put jars in canner. Fill with water to neck of jars. Bring to a boil. Put lid on canner and simmer for 5 minutes. This solution will be enough for 6 to 7 quarts. If you have any left, just use for next batch.

title: salt substitute
directions: Combine all ingredients and use in place of salt to season food.

title: dirty rice
directions: Boil the giblets (gizzards and hearts) in salted water until very tender.
Set aside the water.
Saute the livers in small amount of oil.
Grind or chop the gizzards and liver.
Start the sausage to cooking in a skillet on low heat.
When fat begins to cook out, add the onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic.
Continue cooking on low heat while stirring occasionally, until all the vegetables are soft, then add the giblets and livers and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tempting tuna melts
directions: Mix tuna, dressing, onions, red pepper and seasonings.
For each sandwich, top English muffin half with lettuce, tomato and tuna mixture.
Place on cookie sheet. Broil 1 minute.
Top with 2 process cheese slices.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese begins to melt.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Combine rice-a-roni, excluding seasoning pack, with ground beef and egg.
Shape into meatballs.
Brown on all sides in skillet.
Combine contents of beef seasoning packet with 2 1/2 cups hot water.
Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Thicken gravy, if desired.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Combine shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Beat together thoroughly.
Add flour, salt, soda and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Shape in balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Cool, but don't let it get too cold.
Add crushed pineapple.
Mix sugar with softened cream cheese.
Blend in Cool Whip and all other ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours, but best when chilled overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: better than "sex" cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
In saucepan over medium heat, cook pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes.
Punch holes in hot cake and pour pineapple over it.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Mix instant pudding and pour over cake.
Slice bananas on top of pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: cole slaw(serves 1)
directions: Place chopped cabbage in medium mixing bowl.
Pour heated vinegar and diet sweetener mixture over cabbage; drain.
Sprinkle with pepper before serving.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets.
Cool, peel and rice (about 2 1/4 cups).
In a large pot, have boiling water ready.
In a mixing bowl combine potatoes, flour, salt, farina, egg and milk.
Mix thoroughly until smooth.
Dust hands with flour.
Form into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Drop dumplings into rapidly boiling water.
Boil gently again.
Simmer the dumplings for about 10 minutes or until they rise to the top.
Makes about 12 to 14 dumplings.

title: strawberry glaze
directions: *Use any flavor of jello for kind of pie wanted.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix vegetables and pour salad dressing over all.
Refrigerate overnight and serve with tortilla chips.

title: meat loaf(for 50 people)
directions: Mix ingredients lightly.
Do not overmix.
Place in 5 (4 x 9-inch) loaf pans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Serving:
4 ounces.

title: best lasagne
directions: Brown beef, drain off fat.
Add sauce and water, simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine the eggs, Ricotta or cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour 1 cup of sauce in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer 3 slices of uncooked lasagne noodles over sauce, cover with 1 1/2 cups sauce. Spread one-half of the cheese filling mixture over the sauce, sprinkle on one-half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers of noodles, sauce, cheese filling, Mozzarella cheese and top with layer of noodles and remaining sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, then remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer. Allow to stand at least 10 minutes before cutting to serve.
